WEBVTT

00:36.137 --> 00:39.907
[ Panting ]

00:46.447 --> 00:51.552
[ Thunder Rumbling ]

01:21.682 --> 01:23.684
[ Grunting ]

01:46.174 --> 01:48.342
WHERE ARE YOU ?

01:58.952 --> 02:03.591
OH. HELLO, BEAUTIFUL.

02:03.624 --> 02:05.593
[ Kissing Sound ]

02:05.626 --> 02:08.496
DID YOU MISS ME ?

02:19.740 --> 02:22.676
DAD, I'VE GIVEN THIS
SOME THOUGHT...

02:22.710 --> 02:27.548
AND I'VE DECIDED THAT
SINCE DAMIEN AND RALPH
HAVE THEIR OWN ROOMS,

02:27.581 --> 02:31.885
WELL, THERE'S NO REASON WHY
THEY SHOULD BE BRINGING
THEIR JUNK INTO MY ROOM.

02:31.919 --> 02:33.987
WELL, HOW DOES THAT
SOUND, HELEN ?

02:34.021 --> 02:37.791
- [ Gulping ]
- [ Door Opening ]

02:37.825 --> 02:40.861
OUT OF THE WAY,
STICK BOY !
HAND & FOOT
IS HERE TO STAY.

02:40.894 --> 02:43.497
OOPS, KICKED
YOUR BABY MONKEY.
GET OUT OF HERE, RALPH !

02:43.531 --> 02:47.568
HERE, TAKE THIS.
GO AWAY, DAMIEN.
THIS IS MY ROOM.

02:47.601 --> 02:50.571
WAS. NOW IT'S ALSO
THE WORLD HEADQUARTERS
OF HAND & FOOT, INCORPORATED.

02:50.604 --> 02:53.407
HAND & FOOT
ALL THE WAY !
HAND & FOOT,
HAND & FOOT, HAND & FOOT !

02:53.441 --> 02:58.512
- HAND & FOOT ? YOU GUYS
AREN'T GONNA MAKE A DIME.
- OKAY, WE'LL USE THIS.

02:58.546 --> 03:00.848
YEAH !
HEY, THAT'S
MY LIFE SAVINGS !

03:00.881 --> 03:03.917
CONSIDER YOURSELF
OUR SILENT PARTNER.
YEAH, SAY
SOMETHING AND YOU'RE DEAD.

03:03.951 --> 03:06.387
YEAH.
HOW'S THE BIG MOVE
GOING ?

03:06.420 --> 03:08.389
GREAT.
GOOD.

03:08.422 --> 03:10.591
COME ON, RALPH.
GOTTA GET TO WORK.

03:10.624 --> 03:13.427
DAD ?
[ Clears Throat ]

03:13.461 --> 03:15.696
DAD...

03:15.729 --> 03:18.699
WELL, I'VE GIVEN THIS
A LOT OF THOUGHT,

03:18.732 --> 03:20.701
AND I'VE DECIDED THAT...

03:20.734 --> 03:23.737
S-S-SINCE DAMIEN AND RALPH
HAVE THEIR OWN ROOM--
PRESTON,

03:23.771 --> 03:25.673
THEY NEED THE SPACE
FOR THEIR BUSINESS.

03:25.706 --> 03:28.942
NOT MY SPACE.
YOUNG MAN, IN THIS FAMILY,
INDUSTRY GETS REWARDED.

03:28.976 --> 03:31.445
WHILE YOU'RE IN HERE PLAYING,
YOUR BROTHERS ARE HARD AT WORK.

03:31.479 --> 03:34.848
YEAH, KISSIN' BUTT FOR MONEY.
[ Ralph ] WELL, YOU KNOW
THE GOLDEN RULE.

03:34.882 --> 03:38.686
HE WHO HAS THE GOLD
MAKES THE RULES.
ONE DAY YOU'LL HAVE A JOB.

03:38.719 --> 03:43.524
WHEN I WAS YOUR AGE, I HAD MY
OWN BUSINESS CLEANING WHEELS.
[ Mimicking Dad ]

03:43.557 --> 03:46.627
I WAS PULLING DOWN
100 BUCKS A WEEK
POLISHING CARS.

03:46.660 --> 03:51.465
YOU USED TO SAY 75.
WELL, YOU GOTTA
THINK BIG, PRESTON.

03:51.499 --> 03:53.967
SURPRISE.
[ Brothers ]
WHOA, CHECK IT OUT.

03:54.001 --> 03:56.537
YEAH, IT'S FOR YOUR BUSINESS.
WE HAD A SPARE AT THE OFFICE.

03:56.570 --> 03:59.540
DAMIEN, THE SPEAKERS
ARE OUT IN THE HALL.
HOW DOES IT WORK ?

03:59.573 --> 04:02.543
IT IMITATES HUMAN INTELLIGENCE,
LIKE YOU GUYS.

04:02.576 --> 04:05.446
- PRESTON, MAYBE YOU COULD TEACH
YOUR BROTHERS HOW TO USE IT.
- NOT POSSIBLE.

04:05.479 --> 04:09.483
[ Dad ] THE SOFTWARE WILL
TEACH YOU HOW TO DO EVERYTHING
BUT MAKE LOVE TO A WOMAN.

04:09.517 --> 04:12.486
NOW I KNOW WHAT PROGRAM TO GET
YOUR FATHER FOR CHRISTMAS.
MOM !

04:12.520 --> 04:15.656
OOPS ! UH, HERE.
LET ME HELP YOU WITH THAT.
PRESTON, YOU'RE GONNA BE LATE...

04:15.689 --> 04:19.459
- FOR BUTCH'S BIRTHDAY PARTY.
- WHO WANTS TO CELEBRATE
BUTCH'S BIRTH ?

04:19.493 --> 04:21.728
- [ Dad ] IT'S IMPORTANT
TO GET OUT OF YOUR ROOM MORE.
- [ Brothers ] OUR ROOM.

04:21.762 --> 04:24.465
WELL, GOOD LUCK, GUYS.

04:24.498 --> 04:27.568
[ Computer Beeps, Talks ]
DAMIEN AND RALPH SLEEP...

04:27.601 --> 04:30.771
BUTT TO FACE, BUTT TO FACE,

04:30.804 --> 04:32.773
BUTT TO FACE,
HUH ?
WHO SAID THAT ?

04:32.806 --> 04:35.843
BUTT TO FACE,
BUTT TO FACE,
TYPE "QUIT." HIT "DELETE."

04:35.876 --> 04:40.481
BUTT TO FACE, BUTT TO FACE,
BUTT TO FACE--
TURN IT OFF ! PULL THE PLUG !

04:41.715 --> 04:44.618
OW !
DON'T RUB IT.
BE A MAN.

04:44.652 --> 04:49.390
[ Moaning ]
OUCH !
LITTLE WIMP.

04:52.192 --> 04:56.830
[ Dad ] COME ON, PRESTON.
YOU DON'T WANT TO BE LATE
FOR BUTCH'S BIRTHDAY PARTY.

04:56.864 --> 04:59.600
ARE YOU GONNA HAVE FUN
TODAY ?
[ Preston ]
HOW CAN I, DAD ?

04:59.633 --> 05:02.470
I DON'T HAVE ANY MONEY.
NOW, LOOK.
HERE'S A COUPLE OF BUCKS.

05:02.503 --> 05:04.505
AH, HECK, YOU CAN HAVE FUN
ALL DAY ON THAT.

05:04.538 --> 05:07.341
YOU DON'T GET OUT MUCH,
DO YOU, DAD ?

05:07.375 --> 05:10.811
[ P.A. ]
WELCOME TO FUN LAND.
FUN, FUN, FUN FOR EVERYONE.

05:10.844 --> 05:15.349
WELCOME TO FUN LAND.
FUN, FUN, FUN FOR EVERYONE.

05:15.383 --> 05:17.685
HEY. HEY, MAN.
HEY, BUTCH.

05:17.718 --> 05:20.588
HEY, MAN. YEAH !
HEY, WHAT'S UP ?

05:21.889 --> 05:25.659
OH, LOOK.
IT'S PRESTO THE PESTO.

05:25.693 --> 05:28.161
HELLO, BUTCH.
[ Kids Laughing ]

05:28.195 --> 05:30.464
OH !

05:30.498 --> 05:32.866
- TOKENS !
- [ Kids Cheering ]

05:37.405 --> 05:41.709
- GIVE ME 50. IT'S MY BIRTHDAY.
- FIFTY.

05:41.742 --> 05:43.577
- TWENTY-FIVE, PLEASE.
- TWENTY-FIVE.

05:43.611 --> 05:44.745
- TWENTY-SEVEN.
- TWENTY-SEVEN.

05:44.778 --> 05:47.881
- SIX, PLEASE.
- SIX.

05:47.915 --> 05:50.518
SIX.

05:54.888 --> 05:58.358
COMING ?
I DON'T KNOW.

06:03.531 --> 06:05.699
[ Screaming ]

06:05.733 --> 06:08.469
[ Screaming ]

06:13.607 --> 06:17.377
[ Screaming ]

06:29.590 --> 06:31.525
[ Shouting ]
IT'S GONNA BE AWESOME !

06:31.559 --> 06:34.795
YEAH, LET'S GO
OVER HERE !
THIS ONE !
HURRY !

06:52.480 --> 06:55.148
[ Butch ]
HEY, PRESTON !
HEY, OVER HERE !

06:55.182 --> 06:58.652
HEY, PRESTON,
HOW'S YOUR OSTRICH ?
WATCH OUT !

06:58.686 --> 07:01.455
PRESTON
HAS AN OSTRICH !

07:01.489 --> 07:05.593
HEY, PRESTON,
COME WITH US !

07:05.626 --> 07:08.762
- JUST KIDDING !
- [ Laughing ]

07:23.711 --> 07:25.946
[ Groaning ]

07:25.979 --> 07:29.583
[ Dad ]
DID YOU HAVE FUN
AT BUTCH'S BIRTHDAY PARTY ?

07:29.617 --> 07:32.486
I HAVE A QUESTION.
ARE WE BROKE ?

07:32.520 --> 07:35.489
NO, WE JUST HAVE TO WATCH
OUR SPENDING HABITS.
THAT'S RIGHT.

07:35.523 --> 07:39.493
LIKE WHEN YOUR MOTHER
CALLS HER SISTER BACK EAST
AND TALKS FOR 97 MINUTES.

07:39.527 --> 07:42.496
SO IF WE'RE NOT
POVERTY-STRICKEN,

07:42.530 --> 07:44.698
THERE MUST BE SOME OTHER
REASON I'M SO DEPRIVED.

07:44.732 --> 07:47.935
WE'RE OUTTA HERE !
WHOO !
GOIN' TO THE BALL GAME.

07:47.968 --> 07:51.839
- CAN I GO ?
- WE BOUGHT TICKETS, TOAD.

07:51.872 --> 07:53.473
DAMIEN !
YOU NEED SOME CASH ?

07:53.507 --> 07:55.809
NAH, WE GOT A BUNCH
OF CHANGE.
LATER, PRESTON.

07:55.843 --> 07:58.812
IT'S NOT FAIR.
WHY CAN'T I HAVE ANYTHING ?

07:58.846 --> 08:01.649
WELL, PRESTON, THEY HAVE JOBS,
AND THEY'VE LEARNED TO SAVE.

08:01.682 --> 08:03.817
HOW CAN I SAVE MONEY
IF I DON'T HAVE ANY ?

08:03.851 --> 08:06.620
A PENNY SAVED
IS A PENNY EARNED.

08:06.654 --> 08:08.989
- WHAT DO YOU WANT
FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY ?
- MONEY...

08:09.022 --> 08:11.825
SO I CAN PAY TO HAVE RALPH
AND DAMIEN KNOCKED OFF.

08:11.859 --> 08:14.461
ANYTHING ELSE ?

08:14.494 --> 08:16.897
WELL, MAYBE WE'LL
GIVE HIM ONE OF HIS
BIRTHDAY PRESENTS EARLY.

08:16.930 --> 08:19.933
A GIFT CAME
FROM GRANDMA TODAY.

08:26.439 --> 08:31.444
HMM. WHAT A RIP-OFF !
IT'S A CHECK FOR NOTHING !

08:33.614 --> 08:36.349
I'M HAVING A BAD DAY.

08:36.383 --> 08:38.818
OH, YOUR GRANDMA JUST FORGOT
TO FILL IN HOW MUCH IT WAS FOR,

08:38.852 --> 08:41.688
BUT SHE SIGNED IT
AT THE BOTTOM, SEE ?

08:41.722 --> 08:45.759
IT'S A BLANK CHECK.

08:45.793 --> 08:48.829
WE'LL JUST FILL IN THE AMOUNT.
HOW MUCH DID YOU
GET LAST YEAR, HONEY ?

08:48.862 --> 08:51.832
A THOUSAND.

08:51.865 --> 08:54.401
- TEN DOLLARS.
- WAIT, DAD.
WHAT ABOUT INFLATION ?

08:54.434 --> 08:57.437
- OH, MAKE IT 11.
- [ Muttering ]

08:57.470 --> 09:00.173
YOU'D BE SURPRISED HOW FAST...

09:00.207 --> 09:02.910
ELEVEN DOLLARS CAN GROW
WITH INTEREST.

09:04.745 --> 09:07.848
PRESTON ?
PRESTON ?

09:07.881 --> 09:10.584
[ Preston ]
ELEVEN DOLLARS...

09:10.618 --> 09:14.788
AT 3.45% INTEREST.

09:14.822 --> 09:18.391
[ Computer ]
YOUR ACCOUNT WILL REACH...

09:18.425 --> 09:20.460
ONE MILLION DOLLARS...

09:20.493 --> 09:24.632
IN 342,506 YEARS.

09:24.665 --> 09:27.467
I'M STUCK HERE FOREVER.

09:27.500 --> 09:30.403
[ Dad ]
LIGHTS OUT UP THERE.
WHY ?

09:30.437 --> 09:32.405
MY HOUSE, MY RULES.

09:32.439 --> 09:35.508
"MY HOUSE, MY RULES."

09:37.645 --> 09:42.515
MY OWN HOUSE.

09:47.454 --> 09:50.490
[ Yawning ]

10:02.803 --> 10:06.874
[ Engine Stops,
Car Door Shutting ]

10:10.711 --> 10:13.413
[ Man ]
DAVE, WHO NEEDS ASSETS ?
I'M YOUR ASSET.

10:13.446 --> 10:15.482
I'M A BIG ASSET. OH, C--
[ Man On Phone ]
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU.

10:15.515 --> 10:18.686
DAVE, DAVE. COME ON, COME ON.
WHY ONLY BORROW 150,000 ?

10:18.719 --> 10:20.954
OUR MONEY IS YOUR MONEY.
ROUND IT OFF TO TWO.

10:20.988 --> 10:23.757
DO I QUALIFY ?
OF COURSE YOU QUALIFY
FOR THE LOAN, DAVE.

10:23.791 --> 10:26.626
WE'RE GOLF PARTNERS.

10:28.862 --> 10:30.831
-YOU DON'T LOOK HAPPY TO SEE ME.
-QUIG--

10:30.864 --> 10:33.000
- QUIGLEY.
- QUIGLEY.

10:33.033 --> 10:35.368
THAT'S FUNNY.
I DON'T REMEMBER YOU STUTTERING
ON THE WITNESS STAND.

10:35.402 --> 10:37.470
YOU JUST SANG LIKE A BIRD,
DIDN'T YOU ?
I HAD NO CHOICE, CARL.

10:37.504 --> 10:39.807
I MEAN, LYING IN COURT--
YOU ALSO POINTED AT ME.

10:39.840 --> 10:41.975
- THAT HURT.
- WELL, I WAS UNDER OATH.

10:42.009 --> 10:45.478
I MEAN--
COME HERE.

10:45.512 --> 10:47.480
THE ONLY REASON
YOU'RE ALIVE, BIDERMAN,

10:47.514 --> 10:50.550
IS I KNEW I MIGHT NEED YOU
AGAIN SOMEDAY... LIKE TODAY.

10:50.583 --> 10:53.486
OH, SURE.
YOU NEED A LOAN ?
THE RATES ARE GREAT NOW.

10:53.520 --> 10:56.589
AND YOU GET
A TOASTER.
I DON'T NEED A TOASTER.

10:57.925 --> 11:02.863
BEFORE I WENT AWAY, I PUT
ASIDE A LITTLE NEST EGG.

11:06.867 --> 11:10.637
[ Gasping ]
THESE BILLS, THEY'RE
MARKED CONSECUTIVELY.

11:10.670 --> 11:13.506
THEY'D TRACE THESE
IN A MINUTE.
THAT'S RIGHT.

11:13.540 --> 11:17.010
[ Coughing ]
THAT'S WHERE YOU COME IN,
OLD BUDDY. I WANT NEW BILLS.

11:17.044 --> 11:21.014
WE'RE BACK IN THE S&L BUSINESS,
BIDERMAN.
AH, MONEY LAUNDERING...

11:21.048 --> 11:23.683
IS VERY DIFFICULT
THESE DAYS, CARL.
YOU STILL
DO IT THOUGH, DON'T YOU ?

11:23.717 --> 11:25.685
THAT'S A GOOD-LOOKING FAMILY
RIGHT THERE.

11:25.719 --> 11:27.821
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
HURT THEM, ARE YOU ?

11:27.855 --> 11:30.390
HATE TO HAVE TO.
ALL RIGHT.

11:30.423 --> 11:32.392
HOW DO YOU WANT
TO DO THIS ?

11:32.425 --> 11:34.661
I'LL SEND MY GUY IN TOMORROW
WITH A CHECK FOR A MILLION.
TOMORROW ?

11:34.694 --> 11:38.565
YEP, JUST LIKE THE OLD DAYS.
YOU GIVE HIM THE CASH, UNMARKED,
SEND HIM ON HIS WAY.

11:38.598 --> 11:40.567
WHOM SHOULD I EXPECT ?
WHOM SHOULD--

11:40.600 --> 11:42.836
WHOM SHOULD YOU EXPECT ?
HIS NAME IS JUICE.

11:42.870 --> 11:45.873
JUICE ?
MMM, HE'LL BE HERE
IN EXACTLY 24 HOURS.

11:45.906 --> 11:48.708
LET'S CALL IT 1:00.

11:48.742 --> 11:52.645
COME ON. WALK ME OUT.
SHOW A LITTLE RESPECT.

11:54.547 --> 11:56.549
WHOA.

12:14.935 --> 12:17.404
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

12:55.608 --> 12:59.579
HI.
HI. CAN YOU
SEE OKAY ?

12:59.612 --> 13:02.482
OH, YEAH.
OH, YEAH, SURE.

13:02.515 --> 13:04.651
I WOULD LIKE TO OPEN
AN ACCOUNT, PLEASE.

13:04.684 --> 13:06.954
ELEVEN DOLLARS.

13:06.987 --> 13:10.924
DO YOU HAVE ANY OTHER MONEY
YOU'D LIKE TO DEPOSIT,
MR. WATERS ?

13:10.958 --> 13:12.960
OH, UH, I COULD,

13:12.993 --> 13:15.996
BUT IT'S SORT OF HARD
TO SAVE AROUND MY HOUSE;
THAT'S WHY I'M HERE.

13:16.029 --> 13:19.867
I'M AFRAID WE HAVE
A MINIMUM BALANCE. IT'S $200.

13:19.900 --> 13:22.635
TWO HUNDRED DOLLARS ?

13:22.669 --> 13:25.005
THAT COULD TAKE
A MILLION YEARS.

13:25.038 --> 13:28.942
WELL, WHENEVER YOU'RE READY,
PLEASE COME BACK AND SEE ME.

13:28.976 --> 13:31.344
MY NAME'S SHAY STANLEY.

13:31.378 --> 13:34.848
ASK FOR ME.
OKAY, I'LL DO THAT.

13:35.983 --> 13:40.487
- THANKS.
- BYE-BYE.

13:40.520 --> 13:43.991
- I-I'LL SEE YOU NEXT TIME.
- I HOPE IT'S NOT
IN A MILLION YEARS.

13:44.024 --> 13:47.694
B-BYE-BYE.

13:47.727 --> 13:51.664
[ Biderman ]
EXCUSE ME.
CARL, CARL !

13:51.698 --> 13:54.734
HERE. YOU CAN
USE THESE CHECKS.
THEY'RE TEMPORARY.

13:54.767 --> 13:57.770
THANK YOU, EDWARD.
LIKE OUR RELATIONSHIP.

14:02.842 --> 14:05.012
SUCKER !
GIVE ME THAT !

14:05.045 --> 14:07.714
- [ Laughing ]
- GIVE IT TO ME !

14:10.183 --> 14:12.886
BUTCH, GIVE IT TO ME !

14:14.888 --> 14:17.590
PRESTON, COME ON !
BUTCH !

14:18.858 --> 14:22.462
- GIVE IT BACK ! WHOA !
- IF YOU CAN CATCH ME !

14:25.198 --> 14:26.866
COME ON, BUTCH !

14:28.601 --> 14:30.837
[ Control Panel Dings,
Engine Revs ]

14:30.870 --> 14:34.607
[ Preston Screams ]

14:38.912 --> 14:43.716
- [ Screaming ]
- [ Tires Screeching ]

14:44.884 --> 14:46.954
PERFECT.

14:50.457 --> 14:52.592
WHAT THE HELL DO YOU
THINK YOU'RE DOING ?

14:52.625 --> 14:54.928
I-- I--

14:54.962 --> 14:57.464
HUH ?
[ Butch ]
I SAW THE WHOLE THING.

14:57.497 --> 15:00.433
I CAN BE A WITNESS
IF THE PRICE IS DECENT.
GET OUTTA HERE.

15:00.467 --> 15:03.870
HE'S PERFECTLY ALL RIGHT,
AREN'T YOU ? AREN'T YOU ?

15:03.903 --> 15:07.807
- YES.
- GOOD. GET THAT THING OUT
FROM UNDERNEATH MY CAR.

15:07.840 --> 15:10.643
WHAT ABOUT MY BIKE ?

15:10.677 --> 15:12.645
KID, WAS I THE ONE
THAT PARKED THERE--
OH, MY WORD !

15:12.679 --> 15:16.449
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT ?
HE'S FINE. IT WAS JUST
A LITTLE ACCIDENT. HE'S OKAY.

15:16.483 --> 15:19.719
- I THINK THIS GUY'S
BEEN DRINKING VODKA.
- I HAVE NOT BEEN DRINK--

15:19.752 --> 15:22.956
[ Laughs ]
I DON'T DRINK AT ALL.
SERIOUSLY, SERIOUSLY.

15:22.990 --> 15:25.825
KID, TALK TO ME.
HOW MUCH YOU WANT
FOR THE BIKE ?

15:25.858 --> 15:27.827
- A THOUSAND BUCKS.
- I'M NOT TALKING TO YOU !

15:27.860 --> 15:30.463
BYE, KID.
GO ON. WALK AWAY.

15:30.497 --> 15:33.366
WHAT DO YOU WANT, KID ?
NAME A FIGURE,
WE'LL DISCUSS IT.

15:39.672 --> 15:41.841
GIVE THIS TO YOUR DAD.
HE'LL KNOW WHAT TO DO
WITH IT. I GOTTA GO.

15:43.510 --> 15:45.478
[ Tires Screeching ]

15:45.512 --> 15:47.914
[ Tire Squeaking ]

15:47.947 --> 15:50.150
OH, MAN.

15:50.183 --> 15:52.952
I THOUGHT WE UNDERSTOOD ABOUT
TAKING CARE OF OUR VALUABLES.

15:52.986 --> 15:56.856
VALUABLE ?
IT WAS A PIECE OF JUNK.

15:56.889 --> 15:58.858
IF THAT'S HOW YOU
FEEL ABOUT A GIFT
FROM YOUR PARENTS,

15:58.891 --> 16:00.927
I DON'T SEE
GIVING YOU A NEW ONE
FOR YOUR BIRTHDAY.

16:00.960 --> 16:04.597
I DON'T WANT A NEW BIKE.
I WANT MY OWN ROOM.

16:04.631 --> 16:07.467
I'M WARNING YOU.
YOU'RE ON THIN ICE
AS IT IS ABOUT THE BIKE.

16:07.500 --> 16:09.502
YOU KNOW WHAT I WANT ?

16:09.536 --> 16:13.173
WHAT I WANT
IS MY OWN HOUSE.

16:13.206 --> 16:16.476
MY RULES, MY MONEY.

16:16.509 --> 16:19.512
LISTEN, YOUNG MAN,
UNTIL FURTHER NOTICE,
YOU'RE GROUNDED.

16:24.717 --> 16:27.487
WHAT'D I DO WRONG ?

16:27.520 --> 16:29.722
[ Sighs ]
FRED.

16:36.596 --> 16:38.598
HMM.

16:43.870 --> 16:45.905
IT'S A BLANK CHECK.

17:03.523 --> 17:05.525
** [ Computer Start-Up Tone ]

17:09.862 --> 17:12.898
PRESTON WATERS.

17:15.568 --> 17:17.604
TWO HUNDRED.

17:20.473 --> 17:22.709
HMM.

17:30.217 --> 17:32.452
A THOUSAND.

17:38.958 --> 17:41.594
HMM.

17:52.572 --> 17:55.342
ONE MILLION DOLLARS.

18:13.493 --> 18:16.629
CASH.

18:34.647 --> 18:36.649
WHOA !

18:46.626 --> 18:48.695
ONE MILLION DOLLARS.

19:06.579 --> 19:10.450
[ Electronic Zooming ]

19:10.483 --> 19:12.852
HEY, SONNY.

19:12.885 --> 19:14.854
CASHIN' A BIG ONE TODAY ?

19:14.887 --> 19:17.690
UH, SORT OF.

19:18.825 --> 19:21.828
YOO-HOO.
OVER HERE, YOUNG MAN.

19:26.599 --> 19:30.570
WELL ?
I-I-I'D LIKE TO...

19:30.603 --> 19:32.905
CASH THIS CHECK, PLEASE.

19:41.514 --> 19:46.486
OH, A COMEDIAN.
[ Laughing ]

19:46.519 --> 19:50.523
N-NO, MA'AM.
OKAY, THEN WE BETTER TAKE IT
TO MR. BIDERMAN. COME ON !

19:50.557 --> 19:54.694
[ Ticking ]
[ Door Opening ]

19:57.530 --> 20:01.834
EXCUSE ME, MR. BIDERMAN.
WE HAVE A LITTLE PROBLEM HERE.

20:01.868 --> 20:04.571
WHAT IS IT, MRS. UDOWITZ ?

20:04.604 --> 20:07.840
SOMEONE THINKS THIS IS
SOME KIND OF GAME.
WHAT ?

20:07.874 --> 20:11.378
LET ME SEE THAT.

20:12.745 --> 20:16.583
I SEE.

20:16.616 --> 20:18.851
IS THERE MUCH OF A LINE
OUT THERE, MRS. UDOWITZ ?

20:18.885 --> 20:21.554
YES, WE'RE SWAMPED.
THEN WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE ?

20:21.588 --> 20:24.391
PLEASE.

20:29.896 --> 20:31.898
[ Door Closes ]

20:44.811 --> 20:49.449
- JUICE ?
- NO, THANKS, I'M NOT THIRSTY.

20:49.482 --> 20:52.685
NOT THIRSTY.

20:54.621 --> 20:58.491
MR. QUIGLEY GIVE YOU
THIS CHECK ?

20:58.525 --> 21:00.593
HE DID.

21:00.627 --> 21:02.595
HE DID.

21:02.629 --> 21:05.732
HOW DID YOU
RUN INTO MR. QUIGLEY ?

21:05.765 --> 21:08.868
I DIDN'T.
HE RAN INTO ME.

21:10.370 --> 21:12.372
AHA.

21:19.178 --> 21:21.614
[ Snickering ]

21:21.648 --> 21:24.651
[ Laughing ]
BRILLIANT. BRILLIANT !

21:30.823 --> 21:33.159
- [ Groans ]
- I SUPPOSE YOU WANT BIG BILLS.

21:33.192 --> 21:36.763
ACTUALLY, REGULAR SIZE
WOULD BE OKAY.

21:36.796 --> 21:39.532
REGULAR.
HMM.

21:39.566 --> 21:41.634
THAT'S CUTE.

21:42.835 --> 21:44.837
PUT YOUR BACKPACK
ON THE TABLE.

21:44.871 --> 21:48.375
HEY, HEY.

21:55.515 --> 21:57.884
I ASSUME YOU KNOW
WHAT TO DO WITH THIS.

21:57.917 --> 22:00.487
UH-HUH.
YEAH.
UH-HUH.

22:08.928 --> 22:11.564
NEXT !

22:11.598 --> 22:14.166
LOOK HERE, SWEETHEART.
MMM, YOU'RE LOOKIN'
KIND OF GOOD THERE.

22:14.200 --> 22:16.168
YOU GOT YOUR PEARLS
AND EVERYTHING ON.

22:16.202 --> 22:18.471
HATE FOR SOMETHING
TO HAVE TO HAPPEN TO 'EM.

22:18.505 --> 22:20.807
LOOK HERE,
MY NAME IS JUICE...

22:20.840 --> 22:22.809
AND I GOT SOMETHING RIGHT HERE,
AND I WONDERED...

22:22.842 --> 22:25.845
IF YOU'D BE SO KIND ENOUGH
AS TO CASH IT FOR ME.

22:25.878 --> 22:28.681
WHAT DO YOU WANT ?
A MILLION BUCKS ?

22:28.715 --> 22:32.452
WELL, AS A MATTER OF FACT,
I DO.

22:33.953 --> 22:35.922
[ Sighs ]
GO SEE BIDERMAN.

22:43.430 --> 22:47.366
MM-MM.
OH, MY GOODNESS GRACIOUS.

22:47.400 --> 22:50.470
HERE WE GO.
HERE WE GO.

22:54.974 --> 22:58.878
YOU TELL MR. QUIGLEY THAT
HE HASN'T LOST HIS TOUCH.

22:58.911 --> 23:01.914
UH-HUH.
ALL RIGHT.
YOU CAN GO NOW.

23:04.617 --> 23:06.719
HEY, KID !

23:06.753 --> 23:11.424
- STAY AWAY FROM THE RACETRACK.
- YES, SIR.

23:19.466 --> 23:21.568
GOOD ONE, MAN.
LOOKING GOOD.

23:24.837 --> 23:27.440
MMM. OH !
EXCUSE ME, SWEETIE.

23:27.474 --> 23:30.409
[ Gasps ]

23:30.443 --> 23:32.144
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU,
LITTLE BOY ?
[ Preston ]
I'M SORRY.

23:32.178 --> 23:34.881
DON'T BE MESSIN' UP A VIEW
AS GOOD AS ALL THAT.

23:34.914 --> 23:38.651
I-I'M SORRY.
WHAT YOU DOIN'
OUT OF SCHOOL ANYWAY, HUH ?

23:38.685 --> 23:42.589
YOU KNOW YOU OUGHTA
BE IN SCHOOL.

23:45.625 --> 23:48.461
GO ON AND GET UP OUTTA HERE
BEFORE I START TO GET UPSET.

23:48.495 --> 23:50.830
HURRY UP.

24:09.682 --> 24:11.651
HOW, UH--
HOW MAY I HELP YOU, SIR ?

24:11.684 --> 24:16.355
I'M BIG JUICE, MAN.
QUIGLEY SENT ME.

24:20.627 --> 24:22.595
EVERYTHING IS FINE.

24:22.629 --> 24:24.864
NOT TO WORRY.
UH-HUH.

24:28.200 --> 24:31.470
YEAH !

24:31.504 --> 24:35.508
- THE EAGLE HAS LANDED.
- HMM ?

24:41.848 --> 24:43.916
THE HORSE IS IN THE BARN.

24:49.589 --> 24:52.692
THE CHICKEN...
IS IN THE POT.

24:52.725 --> 24:57.496
LOOK HERE, MAN, I DON'T
KNOW NOTHIN' ABOUT NO EAGLES
LANDIN' AND ALL OF THAT.

24:57.530 --> 24:59.666
I DON'T KNOW NOTHIN'
ABOUT NO HORSE RUNNIN'
THROUGH THE BARN.

24:59.699 --> 25:03.469
AND I CERTAINLY DON'T
KNOW NOTHIN' ABOUT NO...
CHICKENS BEIN' IN THE POT.

25:03.502 --> 25:05.471
YOU UNDERSTAND ?

25:05.504 --> 25:07.840
BUT IF YOU DO ME A FAVOR...

25:07.874 --> 25:10.509
AS TO BE SO KIND AS TO CASH
THIS CHECK RIGHT THERE,

25:10.543 --> 25:13.613
- I COULD BE ON MY WAY.
- WAIT.

25:14.847 --> 25:17.416
- QUIGLEY SENT YOU ?
- THAT'S RIGHT.

25:17.449 --> 25:19.418
- WHAT ABOUT THE KID ?
- WHAT KID ? MAN--

25:19.451 --> 25:21.888
THE KID ! THE KID
WITH THE BACKPACK !

25:21.921 --> 25:24.857
LOOK HERE, MAN.
I'M TIRED OF TELLIN' YOU THIS.

25:24.891 --> 25:27.660
BUT IF YOU DON'T GIVE ME
THE MONEY FOR THAT CHECK,

25:27.694 --> 25:31.931
I GUARANTEE THERE'S A BULLET
WITH YOUR NAME ON IT
IN THIS CHAMBER.

25:31.964 --> 25:36.669
[ Moaning ]
THE KID WITH THE BACKPACK.

25:36.703 --> 25:39.772
THE KID WITH THE BACKPACK !
THE BACKPACK !

25:39.806 --> 25:42.408
THE BACKPACK !
SHIT ! OH, MY GOD !

25:47.479 --> 25:50.416
[ Quigley ]
150 GRAND, CASH.

25:50.449 --> 25:52.919
IT'S MY LAST OFFER, GUYS.
[ Woman ]
YOU'RE OUR REALTOR.

25:52.952 --> 25:57.790
YOU TELL US.
THIS OFFER IS SO MUCH LESS
THAN OUR ASKING PRICE.

25:57.824 --> 26:01.894
WELL, MRS. APPLETON,
IT REALLY IS A BUYER'S MARKET.

26:01.928 --> 26:04.764
DO YOU MIND
IF WE TAKE A MINUTE
TO THINK ABOUT IT ?

26:04.797 --> 26:06.933
LISTEN, I GOT ALL THE TIME
IN THE WORLD, SWEETHEART.

26:06.966 --> 26:10.336
TOO BAD I CAN'T SAY
THE SAME FOR YOU TWO.

26:14.173 --> 26:17.143
APPLESAUCE, WHAT'S
WITH THE LONG FACE, MY MAN ?

26:17.176 --> 26:19.779
I BOUGHT YOUR PAD.
YOU'VE GOT SOME CASH.
IT'S A BEAUTIFUL THING.

26:19.812 --> 26:23.449
SU CASA IS SOON TO BE MI CASA.
YOU KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING ?

26:23.482 --> 26:26.986
GROOVIN' THING, MAN.
YEAH, WELL--

26:27.019 --> 26:29.488
[ Dial Tone ]

26:31.924 --> 26:34.493
** [ Start-Up Tone ]
[ Sighs ]

26:37.697 --> 26:40.566
[ Phone Ringing ]

26:40.599 --> 26:43.636
- HELLO.
- [ Computer ] GOOD AFTERNOON.

26:43.670 --> 26:44.837
...YOUR HOUSE.
[ Computer Beeps ]

26:44.871 --> 26:48.474
I'D LIKE TO MAKE
A CASH OFFER ON YOUR HOUSE.

26:48.507 --> 26:50.910
SOMEONE ELSE
WANTS TO MAKE AN OFFER.

26:50.943 --> 26:53.646
WHAT ?
ON THIS DUMP ?

26:53.680 --> 26:56.582
UH, HELLO, SIR.
CAN YOU HEAR ME ?
WHO IS THIS YO-YO ?

26:56.615 --> 26:58.985
[ Typing ]

26:59.018 --> 27:02.454
- [ Computer ] ONE-SIXTY.
- WHAT KIND OF HUSTLE IS THIS ?

27:02.488 --> 27:04.891
AND WHAT'S WITH
YOUR VOICE, PAL ?

27:07.626 --> 27:10.863
SORE THROAT-ITIS.
[ Computer Coughs ]

27:10.897 --> 27:16.602
YEAH. I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.
ONE-SEVENTY RIGHT NOW, CASH,
AND I WALK AWAY.

27:16.635 --> 27:19.538
YOU TAKE IT OR LEAVE IT
RIGHT NOW.
ASK THE BOX.

27:20.807 --> 27:24.977
ONE-EIGHTY,
PLUS CLOSING COSTS.

27:25.011 --> 27:27.146
ONE-EIGHTY,
[ Preston ]
TOP THAT, SUCKER.

27:27.179 --> 27:30.149
PLUS CLOSING COSTS.

27:30.182 --> 27:32.651
- ONE-NINETY, DARLIN'.
TOP THAT.
- PRESTON, HONEY ?

27:32.685 --> 27:35.154
I HAVE A FEW ERRANDS TO RUN.
I'LL BE BACK BY 2:00.

27:35.187 --> 27:37.356
OKAY.
BYE, MOM.

27:41.593 --> 27:43.696
[ Computer ]
TWO HUNDRED.
TWO-TEN.

27:43.730 --> 27:46.532
- JUST TO BE SAFE,
MAKE THAT 3:00.
- [ Laughs ]

27:46.565 --> 27:49.702
- THREE HUNDRED ?
- MA, YOU'RE KILLIN' ME
ON THIS DEAL.

27:49.736 --> 27:51.704
COME ON. ARE YOU
TELLIN' ME WE'RE GONNA
SIT HERE AND LISTEN...

27:51.738 --> 27:54.473
TO SOME TALKING BOX
WITH A ROBOT VOICE ?
WHAT IS THIS ?

27:54.506 --> 27:58.510
UH, 300 IT IS. ARE YOU
PREPARED TO TOP 300 ?

27:58.544 --> 28:01.580
NO, I DON'T THINK
I'M PREPARED TO TOP 300 !
ARE YOU OUT OF YOUR MIND ?

28:01.613 --> 28:04.817
WE HAD A DEAL HERE !
ARE YOU REALTORS JUST A BUNCH
OF CROOKS ? IS THAT IT ?

28:04.851 --> 28:06.753
WHAT'S GOING ON
WITH YOU PEOPLE ?

28:06.786 --> 28:09.155
WELL, I AM SORRY
YOU FEEL THAT WAY,

28:09.188 --> 28:11.557
BUT I HAVE AN OFFER
ON THE TABLE OF 300.

28:11.590 --> 28:13.893
- [ Computer ] THOUSAND.
- UH, WE'LL TAKE IT.

28:13.926 --> 28:16.729
- SOLD.
- YEAH.

28:16.763 --> 28:19.732
YOU PROBABLY WON'T LIVE
TO ENJOY THE CASH.

28:21.868 --> 28:24.670
[ Realtor ]
JUST ONE THING, SIR.
WHAT IS YOUR NAME ?

28:24.703 --> 28:29.375
MY NAME IS PRESTON--

28:37.616 --> 28:39.886
BINGO.

28:42.755 --> 28:44.791
MACINTOSH.

28:44.824 --> 28:47.860
MY NAME IS MACINTOSH.

28:47.894 --> 28:50.596
WELL, CONGRATULATIONS,
MR. MACINTOSH.

28:50.629 --> 28:54.801
- YOU HAVE A HOUSE.
- YES !

28:57.603 --> 28:59.806
I'M RICH !

28:59.839 --> 29:03.642
YEAH !

29:03.675 --> 29:05.677
WHOO, YES !

29:07.847 --> 29:10.582
YEAH !

29:10.616 --> 29:13.519
MONEY !
MONEY !

29:15.621 --> 29:18.590
YOU DID WHAT WITH MY MONEY ?
[ Juice ] YOU'RE NOT
GONNA BELIEVE THIS.

29:18.624 --> 29:22.929
HE GAVE ALL YOUR MONEY
TO A LITTLE OLD BITTY BOY.

29:22.962 --> 29:25.764
THAT WAS MY NEST EGG.
THAT'S ALL I HAD TO START
A NEW LIFE.

29:25.798 --> 29:28.434
I WORKED HARD TO STEAL
THAT MONEY, BIDERMAN !

29:28.467 --> 29:30.569
YOU GAVE IT TO SOME
ZIT-FACED LITTLE KID ?

29:30.602 --> 29:32.771
NOW WAIT A MINUTE.
I SEEN THE KID.

29:32.805 --> 29:36.442
HIS SKIN LOOKED PRETTY
SMOOTH.
THE BOY HAD A CHECK
SIGNED BY YOU.

29:36.475 --> 29:38.845
I DIDN'T WRITE
A CHECK TO ANYBODY EXCEPT
FOR THIS GENIUS HERE.

29:38.878 --> 29:40.847
NOW HOLD ON A MINUTE.

29:40.880 --> 29:43.149
I'M NOT THE ONE WHO CASHED
A CHECK FOR A MILLION DOLLARS.

29:43.182 --> 29:45.651
THAT WAS THIS MAN
RIGHT HERE.
HAD YOUR SIGNATURE.

29:45.684 --> 29:47.987
I SAID I DIDN'T WRITE IT !
YOU GAVE ME THE CHECKBOOK,

29:48.020 --> 29:51.858
I PUT IT IN MY POCKET,
I GOT IN MY CAR, I--

29:51.891 --> 29:56.162
I-- I CAN'T
FEEL MY LEGS.

29:56.195 --> 29:59.465
UH, I--
OH, OH, OH.

29:59.498 --> 30:03.802
CALM DOWN. I'VE GOT
A SURVEILLANCE PHOTO
OF THE BOY.

30:03.836 --> 30:06.472
[ Stammering ]
WE'LL FIND HIM
IN NO TIME.

30:06.505 --> 30:08.440
OH, YEAH,
THAT'S HIM.
I CAN'T SEE A THING.

30:08.474 --> 30:10.776
I RECOGNIZE HIM.
I'D KNOW HIM ANYWHERE.

30:10.809 --> 30:12.811
IT'S UPSIDE-DOWN.

30:17.884 --> 30:23.589
ALL RIGHT. SO WHERE
ARE YOU GONNA FIND THE KID,
MR. FAMILY MAN ?

30:24.891 --> 30:28.995
- NEWSPAPERS.
- YOU WANT ME TO ADVERTISE,
IS THAT IT ?

30:29.028 --> 30:31.463
NO, NO, NO.
THEY HAVE LISTINGS.

30:31.497 --> 30:36.568
UH, FAMILY ACTIVITIES
WHERE, WHERE-- YOU KNOW,
THINGS WHERE KIDS GO. SEE ?

30:36.602 --> 30:39.671
FINE. YOU'RE GONNA
HELP ME FIND HIM.

30:39.705 --> 30:43.575
YOU UNDERSTAND ?
DEAD OR ALIVE.
UH-HUH.

30:43.609 --> 30:45.844
LET'S GET OUT OF HERE.

30:47.513 --> 30:49.781
OH, DON'T THINK
YOU AIN'T COMIN' WITH US.
[ Gasping ]

30:52.018 --> 30:55.721
SOMEBODY'S IN THERE
WITH BIDERMAN NOW.

30:55.754 --> 30:58.724
A COUPLE OF GUYS
I'VE NEVER SEEN BEFORE.
THEY'VE JUST LEFT.

30:58.757 --> 31:00.759
THE MONEY LAUNDERING
IS DEFINITELY ON AGAIN.

31:00.792 --> 31:03.529
WE'VE GOT TO NOTIFY
THE BUREAU RIGHT AWAY.

31:08.434 --> 31:11.670
[ Man ]
HELLO, LIMOUSINES UNLIMITED.

31:11.703 --> 31:14.706
YOU HAVE THE CAR KEYS ?
NO, YOU HAVE
THE CAR KEYS.

31:14.740 --> 31:16.575
OH, YEAH. YOU MAKE SURE
YOU-KNOW-WHO STAYS GROUNDED.
AND HE GOES TO BED EARLY.

31:16.608 --> 31:19.611
YOU GOT IT, POPS.
DON'T CALL ME THAT.

31:36.162 --> 31:38.430
UH, EXCUSE ME.

31:38.464 --> 31:40.432
SORRY, KID.
NOBODY FAMOUS INSIDE.

31:40.466 --> 31:42.601
DO YOU WANT TO TAKE YOUR MITTS
OFF THE CAR, PLEASE ?

31:42.634 --> 31:45.571
I'M WAITIN'
FOR A CLIENT HERE.
BUT I'M YOUR CLIENT.

31:45.604 --> 31:48.941
OH, RIGHT, YEAH.
AND I'M MADONNA.

31:48.975 --> 31:51.710
SORRY, KID. THE BOSS
DOESN'T LIKE ME TAKING
BASEBALL CARDS AS PAYMENT.

31:51.743 --> 31:54.546
SO IF YOU WANT TO RIDE IN THIS,
YOU NEED SOME BUCKAROOS,
BUCKARINIS,

31:54.580 --> 31:57.616
SOME MOOLA, SOME DINERO,
SOME MONEY, SOME FROGSKINS,

31:57.649 --> 31:59.618
MUCH SIMILAR TO THE MONEY
YOU'VE GIVEN ME--

31:59.651 --> 32:01.820
IN FACT, IDENTICAL TO THE MONEY
YOU'VE GIVEN ME RIGHT NOW.

32:01.853 --> 32:04.156
I WAS JUST KIDDIN'
ABOUT BEIN' MADONNA.

32:04.190 --> 32:06.592
MY NAME'S HENRY.
HI, HENRY.
I'M PRESTON.

32:06.625 --> 32:08.594
PRESTON, GOOD TO SEE YA.
PRESTON WATERS.

32:08.627 --> 32:11.897
YES, NICE TO MEET YA.
HOP IN.

32:11.930 --> 32:14.700
GO AHEAD.

32:15.801 --> 32:19.805
I DIDN'T ACTUALLY
MEAN HOP IN, BUT--

32:19.838 --> 32:22.641
SO, WHERE TO,
BOSS ?

32:22.674 --> 32:26.645
WELL, HARRY, WE'RE GONNA
GO BUY SOME STUFF.
YES, SIR.

32:26.678 --> 32:29.448
[ Tires Screeching ]

32:29.481 --> 32:33.485
* HEY, YEAH

32:36.022 --> 32:39.625
* OW, WHOO

32:39.658 --> 32:43.595
* THE BEST THINGS IN LIFE
ARE FREE *

32:43.629 --> 32:46.698
* BUT YOU CAN KEEP THEM
FOR THE BIRDS AND BEES *

32:46.732 --> 32:49.835
* NOW GIVE ME MONEY
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

32:49.868 --> 32:53.839
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT, YEAH
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

32:53.872 --> 32:58.477
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT
YEAH *
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

32:58.510 --> 33:01.547
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

33:01.580 --> 33:06.152
* BABY, YOUR LOVIN'
GIVES ME A THRILL *

33:06.185 --> 33:08.687
* BUT YOUR LOVIN'
NEVER PAID MY BILLS *

33:08.720 --> 33:13.159
* NOW GIVE ME MONEY
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

33:13.192 --> 33:15.727
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

33:15.761 --> 33:18.864
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT
* THAT'S

33:18.897 --> 33:20.866
* WHAT I WANT

33:20.899 --> 33:23.569
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

33:23.602 --> 33:26.572
* GIVE IT TO ME, BABY
UH-HUH *

33:26.605 --> 33:29.408
* OH
* MONEY

33:29.441 --> 33:32.678
* I WANT M-M-M-M-MONEY
YEAH *

33:32.711 --> 33:34.880
* I GOT TO HAVE SOME MONEY

33:34.913 --> 33:37.483
* I WANT TO HAVE THE MONEY
UH-HUH, HEY, HEY *
* MONEY

33:37.516 --> 33:39.651
* HEY, YEAH

33:39.685 --> 33:43.355
* MONEY DON'T GET EVERYTHING
IT'S TRUE *

33:43.389 --> 33:46.158
* WHAT IT DON'T GET NOW
I CAN'T USE *

33:46.192 --> 33:49.895
* I WANT M-M-M-MONEY, HEY
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

33:49.928 --> 33:53.499
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

33:53.532 --> 33:58.404
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

33:58.437 --> 34:01.773
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT
HEY, YEAH *

34:01.807 --> 34:05.877
* I WANT SOME MONEY
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

34:05.911 --> 34:09.447
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT
* HEY, YEAH

34:09.481 --> 34:11.917
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

34:11.949 --> 34:16.855
* MONEY
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT

34:16.888 --> 34:19.958
* THAT'S WHAT I WANT
* OW, HEY

34:19.991 --> 34:23.462
ICE CREAM !
TURN AROUND, HENRY.
OH, RIGHT ON.

34:23.495 --> 34:28.434
* I NEED SOME MONEY, BABY
I NEED SOME MONEY *

34:28.467 --> 34:31.137
* I JUST NEED A FEW *

34:31.170 --> 34:35.407
HEY, THANKS A LOT
FOR THE GREAT WATCH.
YOU'RE WELCOME.

34:35.440 --> 34:39.411
HEY, THIS GUY, UH--
WHAT IS IT ? McINTYRE ?
MACINTOSH.

34:39.445 --> 34:41.813
UH, MACINTOSH.
YEAH, YEAH.

34:41.847 --> 34:44.449
IF YOU DON'T MIND ME ASKIN',
WHERE DOES HE GET HIS MONEY ?

34:44.483 --> 34:47.585
WELL, HE DOESN'T GET IT,
HE JUST HAS IT.

34:47.619 --> 34:51.456
WHY DOES HE GET A KID
LIKE YOU TO GO OUT AND BUY
ALL THIS STUFF FOR HIM ?

34:51.489 --> 34:53.824
HE-- HE NEVER
HAD A REAL CHILDHOOD.

34:53.859 --> 34:56.962
SO NOW THAT HE'S
REALLY, REALLY RICH,

34:56.995 --> 35:00.799
HE CAN HAVE ALL THE FUN
THAT HE COULDN'T HAVE
WHEN HE WAS A KID.

35:00.832 --> 35:03.835
OH. OH, I SEE.
YOU KNOW.

35:03.869 --> 35:06.672
SO HE DIDN'T HAVE ANY
FUN WHEN HE WAS A KID,

35:06.705 --> 35:08.674
BUT NOW HE'S OLD
AND HE'S GOT MONEY.

35:08.707 --> 35:10.776
YOU'RE A KID HAVING
THE FUN FOR HIM NOW...

35:10.809 --> 35:12.844
THAT HE COULDN'T HAVE
WHEN HE WAS A KID.

35:12.878 --> 35:16.582
OKAY, SURE.
STOP ! PULL OVER, HENRY !
IT'S SHAY !

35:16.615 --> 35:18.984
- STOP ! HEY !
- [ Shay Screams ]
YOU SCARED ME !

35:19.017 --> 35:22.654
- SORRY.
- PRESTON, RIGHT ?

35:22.688 --> 35:25.157
YOU'VE GOT
A GOOD MEMORY.
THANKS.

35:25.191 --> 35:27.659
GREAT, KID.
VERY NICE.
NICE WHEELS.

35:27.693 --> 35:31.597
OH, THIS ?
AH, IT'S MY BOSS,
MR. MACINTOSH.

35:31.630 --> 35:35.667
DO YOU WANT
A RIDE ?
NO, THANKS.
I'M OUTTA SHAPE.

35:35.701 --> 35:37.603
NOT FROM WHERE
I'M SITTIN' YOU AREN'T.

35:37.636 --> 35:40.806
SO, UH, I'M THINKIN' ABOUT
COMIN' INTO THE BANK TOMORROW...

35:40.839 --> 35:44.543
AND OPENING MY ACCOUNT.
WOW, YOU GOT
THE $200 ALREADY ?

35:44.576 --> 35:48.714
- JUST ABOUT.
- ALL RIGHT. WELL,
SEE YOU TOMORROW.

35:48.747 --> 35:51.817
- BYE.
- BYE.

35:57.523 --> 35:59.491
WAS THAT HIM ?
WAS THAT BIDERMAN ?

35:59.525 --> 36:02.861
NO, SOME KID WHO CAME
INTO THE BANK TODAY.
NICE WHEELS FOR A KID.

36:02.894 --> 36:05.797
YEAH. SAYS IT
BELONGS TO HIS BOSS,
A GUY NAMED MACINTOSH.

36:05.831 --> 36:09.535
MACINTOSH.
WHEN ARE WE GONNA
SEE BIDERMAN ?

36:12.838 --> 36:15.607
[ Man ]
IT LOOKS LIKE A CIRCUS.

36:23.682 --> 36:27.653
HEY. HEY, HEY, MOVE IT.
I'VE GOT WORK TO DO TOO,
YOU KNOW.

36:27.686 --> 36:31.156
WHERE AM I SUPPOSED TO GO ?
YOU SEE AN OPENING ? HUH ?

36:31.189 --> 36:33.158
HEY, WHAT'S
THE HOLDUP HERE ?

36:33.191 --> 36:35.827
YEAH, SAME TO YOU,
BUDDY.
HEY, MOVE IT !

36:35.861 --> 36:38.664
WHAT IS ALL THIS ?

36:38.697 --> 36:40.699
WHAT A MESS.

36:42.601 --> 36:45.371
THIS IS ABSOLUTE MADNESS !

36:47.473 --> 36:49.741
YO, WHO'S IN CHARGE HERE ?

36:51.577 --> 36:55.414
[ Preston Over Speaker ]
YOU WITH THE RACE CAR,
PUT IT IN THE BACKYARD.

36:55.447 --> 36:58.717
UH, THE WATER SLIDE
GOES BACK BY THE POOL.

36:58.750 --> 37:02.454
YOU GUYS WITH THE TVs,
PUT THEM IN THE LIVING ROOM.

37:02.488 --> 37:05.691
HEY, YOU WITH THE CADILLAC,
OUT BY THE POOL.

37:05.724 --> 37:08.627
YOU IN THE GREEN JUMPSUITS,
BRING THAT AROUND THE BACK.

37:08.660 --> 37:10.896
- PRESTON ?
- HI, DAD.

37:10.929 --> 37:13.699
- WHAT'S GOING ON HERE ?
- MOVIN' IN.

37:13.732 --> 37:16.802
- WHO IS MOVING IN ?
- MACINTOSH.

37:16.835 --> 37:19.805
- WHO'S MACINTOSH ?
- I'LL BE RIGHT WITH YOU, DAD.

37:19.838 --> 37:22.874
COME ON, BOYS.
I DON'T HAVE ALL DAY.

37:22.908 --> 37:26.144
OKAY, MR. WATERS,
THE SECURITY SYSTEM
IS ALL IN PLACE.

37:26.177 --> 37:28.146
EXCUSE ME.
THIS IS THE REMOTE.

37:28.179 --> 37:30.382
HERE ARE
THE INSTRUCTIONS.
ALL RIGHT ?

37:30.416 --> 37:32.884
WE APPRECIATE
MR. MACINTOSH'S BUSINESS.
HERE YOU GO, PAL.

37:32.918 --> 37:35.454
WHAT'S WITH
ALL THE SECURITY ?

37:35.487 --> 37:38.457
MR. MACINTOSH SAYS YOU CAN
NEVER BE TOO PARANOID, DAD.

37:38.490 --> 37:42.894
WELL, WHO IS MACINTOSH ?
I WORK FOR HIM.
HE'S PAYING ME.

37:42.928 --> 37:44.896
YEAH, BUT WHO IS HE ?
I NEVER MET HIM.

37:44.930 --> 37:48.567
YOU MEAN YOU HAVEN'T
MET HIM ?
NO, I HAVEN'T MET HIM.

37:48.600 --> 37:50.936
HE'S HEARD ABOUT YOU.
REALLY ?

37:50.969 --> 37:54.406
YEAH, ABOUT WORK AND STUFF.
REALLY GOOD THINGS.

37:54.440 --> 37:59.611
WELL-- HIS STUFF IS
BLOCKING OUR DRIVEWAY.
DAD.

37:59.645 --> 38:02.914
BOYS !

38:02.948 --> 38:05.984
COULD YOU CLEAR A PATH,
PLEASE ?

38:06.017 --> 38:09.455
GET A MOVE ON IT !

38:12.190 --> 38:14.493
ALL SET, DAD.

38:15.794 --> 38:17.829
* I KNEW A GUY WHO WAS TOUGH
BUT SWEET *

38:17.863 --> 38:20.666
[ Henry ]
GO, GO, GO, GO, GO, GO, GO !

38:20.699 --> 38:24.803
* HE'S THE ONE
HE CAN'T BE BEAT *

38:24.836 --> 38:28.974
* HE'S GOT EVERYTHING
THAT I DESIRE *

38:29.007 --> 38:33.445
* SETS THE SUMMER SUN
ON FIRE *
BRAKE, BRAKE !

38:33.479 --> 38:36.682
* I WANT CANDY

38:38.550 --> 38:42.788
- * I WANT CANDY
- FLIP, FLIP, FLIP, FLIP, FLIP !

38:42.821 --> 38:44.690
* YEAH
[ Game ]
BODY BLOW. UPPERCUT.

38:44.723 --> 38:47.793
BODY BLOW. LEFT HOOK.
UPPERCUT. BODY BLOW.
OW.

38:47.826 --> 38:51.697
UPPERCUT.
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON !

38:51.730 --> 38:54.566
BODY BLOW.
TEN, NINE--

38:54.600 --> 38:56.902
* I WANT CANDY
YEAH ! YES !

38:59.204 --> 39:03.575
* I WANT CANDY

39:03.609 --> 39:06.578
* GO TO SEE HIM
WHEN THE SUN GOES DOWN *

39:06.612 --> 39:10.649
COME ON, HENRY ! COME ON !
* AIN'T NO FINER BOY
IN TOWN *

39:10.682 --> 39:13.552
- HEY ! WHOA !
- * I WANT CANDY

39:13.585 --> 39:18.424
- OH, HENRY !
- * I WANT CANDY

39:18.457 --> 39:22.861
THE BLOOD RUSHED
TO MY HEAD.
* HEY

39:22.894 --> 39:24.863
* HEY

39:24.896 --> 39:26.865
* HEY

39:26.898 --> 39:30.536
* HEY, HEY *

39:32.604 --> 39:34.573
[ Woman ]
IS SOMETHING WRONG ?

39:34.606 --> 39:37.443
NO. I WAS WONDERING
WHO COULD SPEND CASH
LIKE THAT THESE DAYS.

39:37.476 --> 39:39.578
OH, YEAH.
THE MAN'S NAME
IS MACINTOSH.

39:39.611 --> 39:42.448
MACINTOSH ?
MM-HMM.
HE JUST MOVED HERE.

39:42.481 --> 39:45.517
APPARENTLY LOADED.
APPARENTLY.

39:45.551 --> 39:49.187
I DON'T FEEL GOOD
ABOUT BEING HERE.
PEOPLE MAY GET THE WRONG IDEA.

39:49.220 --> 39:51.122
REALLY ?
YOU DON'T FEEL GOOD ?

39:51.156 --> 39:53.425
HOW DO YOU THINK
I FELT WHEN YOU GAVE AWAY
MY MILLION DOLLARS, HUH ?

39:53.459 --> 39:56.127
JUICE. SEE ANYBODY
THAT LOOKS LIKE HIM ?

39:56.161 --> 40:00.732
OH, YEAH. HE LOOKS
LIKE HIM. UH, SHE LOOKS
LIKE HIM RIGHT THERE.

40:00.766 --> 40:04.570
WAY BACK OVER THERE,
UH, THERE GOES HIS LITTLE
TWIN BROTHER.

40:04.603 --> 40:07.773
YOU GIVE ME ONE PICTURE
AND EXPECT ME TO FIND HIM
OUT OF ALL THESE KIDS ?

40:07.806 --> 40:11.443
YOU MUST BE CRAZY. I'M
GONNA GET ON THE WATER SLIDE.
I'M STARTIN' TO SWEAT.

40:11.477 --> 40:13.579
HEY, MISTER, YOU KNOW
WHERE THE REFRESHMENT
STANDS ARE ?

40:13.612 --> 40:15.581
[ Pops Balloon ]
NO.

40:15.614 --> 40:17.783
[ Girl Crying ]

40:17.816 --> 40:20.786
BOOM, BOOM, BOOM !
I GOT YOU !

40:20.819 --> 40:23.388
BOOM, BOOM,
BOOM, BOOM !

40:23.421 --> 40:28.760
[ Electronic Gunfire ]

40:30.696 --> 40:33.632
[ Butch Whimpering ]
HE SAYS HE KNOWS YOU, BOSS.

40:33.665 --> 40:36.401
OH, WELL, JUST THROW HIM OUT.

40:36.434 --> 40:38.136
[ Screaming ]
OW ! OW !

40:38.169 --> 40:43.441
BANZAI !
* I WANT CANDY

40:43.475 --> 40:46.712
[ Preston Screaming ]
* I WANT CANDY

40:48.780 --> 40:50.816
* HEY

40:50.849 --> 40:53.418
* HEY

40:53.451 --> 40:55.987
* HEY *
HIYA.

40:56.021 --> 40:58.423
I DIDN'T EXPECT
TO SEE YOU HERE.

40:58.456 --> 41:02.594
-OH, WHAT YOU DOIN' HERE ?
-I CAME BY TO SEE MR. MACINTOSH.

41:02.628 --> 41:06.632
- OH, NO, HE'S IN A MEETING.
- THAT'S OKAY, I'LL WAIT.
I JUST REALLY NEED TO SEE HIM.

41:06.665 --> 41:08.834
- HE'S IN MEETINGS ALL DAY.
- ALL DAY ?

41:08.867 --> 41:11.803
- SWAMPED.
- HEY, I MISSED YOU AT THE BANK.

41:11.837 --> 41:15.140
I THOUGHT YOU WERE GONNA
COME BY AND SEE ME ABOUT
OPENING UP AN ACCOUNT.

41:15.173 --> 41:19.545
OH, I HAD TO WORK.
WOW. THIS IS
WHERE YOU WORK ?

41:19.578 --> 41:23.649
- NOT TOO SHABBY.
- COMFORTABLE.
I BROUGHT AN APPLICATION.

41:23.682 --> 41:26.818
DO YOU STILL WANT TO OPEN UP
AN ACCOUNT WITH ME ?
YEAH.

41:26.852 --> 41:30.556
- OKAY.
DO YOU HAVE YOUR DEPOSIT ?
- I'LL GO GET IT.

41:30.589 --> 41:33.358
OKAY. GREAT.

41:40.999 --> 41:46.504
[ Preston Screaming ]

41:46.538 --> 41:50.709
WHOA !
THAT'S AMAZING !

41:50.742 --> 41:52.711
SORRY, JUST PRINTED IT.

41:52.744 --> 41:56.582
TWO HUNDRED DOLLARS.
LOOKS LIKE YOU FELL INTO
SOME MONEY, HUH ?

41:56.615 --> 42:00.418
I MAKE A LIVING.
YEAH, WELL, I GUESS
MR. MACINTOSH--

42:00.451 --> 42:02.420
HE KNOWS A GOOD MAN
WHEN HE SEES ONE.

42:02.453 --> 42:05.557
WILL HE BE OPENING UP
AN ACCOUNT WITH US ?
UH, MAYBE.

42:05.591 --> 42:08.159
YEAH ? GREAT. YOU KNOW,
I'D LOVE TO MEET HIM.
HOW'S TONIGHT ?

42:08.193 --> 42:10.896
UH, TONIGHT.
WHAT'S TONIGHT ?
TONIGHT'S WEDNESDAY.

42:10.929 --> 42:14.432
WEDNESDAY.

42:14.465 --> 42:16.768
WEDNESDAY.
I'M SORRY, HE'S BUSY.

42:16.802 --> 42:20.706
- TOO BAD.
- UH, BUT I'M NOT.

42:20.739 --> 42:23.374
OH, I HANDLE
ALL HIS FINANCIAL AFFAIRS.

42:23.408 --> 42:25.711
YOU DO ?
NOT ALL OF THEM,

42:25.744 --> 42:29.781
BUT I CAN
TELL YOU A LOT ABOUT HIM,
SORT OF LIKE A PRE-MEETING.

42:29.815 --> 42:32.951
- AND HE WOULDN'T MIND ?
- HASN'T COMPLAINED YET.

42:32.984 --> 42:36.454
OKAY. I'LL COME BY
AROUND 8:00.

42:36.487 --> 42:38.857
OKAY. WAIT, I COULD
SEND A CAR FOR YOU.

42:38.890 --> 42:43.128
OKAY. COOL.
IT'S A DATE THEN.
BYE-BYE.

42:43.161 --> 42:46.431
A DATE ?

42:46.464 --> 42:48.867
A DATE ?

42:48.900 --> 42:51.703
I'VE NEVER BEEN ON A DATE.

42:51.737 --> 42:54.706
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY CALL ME
DOWNTOWN ? THE BABE-MEISTER.

42:54.740 --> 42:56.808
THINK ABOUT IT.

42:56.842 --> 43:01.446
OKAY, I'M GONNA TELL YOU
ABOUT THE REAL DEAL
ON DATING, WHICH I KNOW.

43:01.479 --> 43:04.716
FIRST OF ALL, WOMEN LOVE
A GREAT BODY. THEY LOVE--
LOOK AT THIS BOD.

43:04.750 --> 43:07.786
WHOA.
SEE ?
YEAH, YEAH.

43:07.819 --> 43:11.456
OF COURSE, YOU'VE GOT A BOD NOW
THAT'S OF A GREEK GOD. REALLY.
THINK ABOUT IT.

43:11.489 --> 43:13.792
WOMEN LIKE YOU TO HAVE
A GOOD BOD BECAUSE THEY WANT
TO FEEL THEY'RE PROTECTED.

43:13.825 --> 43:16.461
YOU MIGHT HAVE TO FIGHT
SOME GUY, YOU KNOW ?
BUT NOT WITH THOSE ARMS.

43:16.494 --> 43:19.898
YOU DON'T WANT TO HIT A GUY WITH
THOSE ARMS 'CAUSE THOSE PYTHONS
WOULD TAKE A GUY'S HEAD OFF.

43:19.931 --> 43:22.600
SERIOUSLY.
YOU'RE BUFF, BUT WE'RE
GONNA GET YOU CHISELED.

43:22.634 --> 43:26.437
OKAY ? OH, WAIT.
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA.

43:26.471 --> 43:28.439
I'M HAVING A VISION
HERE OF A DATE.

43:28.473 --> 43:30.809
THE PERFECT DATE
FOR YOU GUYS.
UH, STEAK HEAVEN !

43:30.842 --> 43:35.513
HO, HO ! MY LITTLE FRIEND,
YOU REALLY HAVE THE HOTS
FOR THIS ONE, HUH ?

43:35.546 --> 43:37.482
YOU KNOW, IF YOU REALLY
WANT TO GO UPSCALE,

43:37.515 --> 43:40.786
THAT ALL-YOU-CAN-EAT SALAD BAR--
WOMEN LOVE THAT.

43:40.819 --> 43:44.856
AND TAKE SOME WITH YOU.
YOU KNOW, LINE YOUR POCKETS
WITH PLASTIC BAGS.

43:44.890 --> 43:49.494
PUT THE FOOD IN THERE.
'CAUSE IT DOESN'T SAY
"ALL YOU CAN EAT HERE."

43:49.527 --> 43:51.763
DOES IT SAY "HERE"
ON THE SIGN ?
I DON'T THINK SO.

43:51.797 --> 43:54.966
SO YOU TAKE SOMETHING
BACK FOR LATER.
A LITTLE SNACKAROO.

43:55.000 --> 43:59.170
OH, WOMEN LOVE THAT.
YOU GET HOME AND YOU GOT
A POCKETFUL OF HOT WINGS.

43:59.204 --> 44:01.840
THERE'S NOTHING MORE
THAT IMPRESSES A WOMAN.

44:01.873 --> 44:04.142
GET YOURSELF SOME FLOWERS.
GET YOURSELF A GREAT BODY,

44:04.175 --> 44:06.144
SOME NICE HAIR,
SOME GOOD CLOTHES, A CAR,

44:06.177 --> 44:08.146
AND LEARN TO SAY WORDS
LIKE "NONCOMMITTAL."

44:08.179 --> 44:10.949
YOU ARE A DATE
AND A HALF, PAL.

44:10.982 --> 44:15.653
* THERE HE IS
SOME TINY TIM *

44:15.687 --> 44:19.357
* THERE HE IS
SIX FOOT AND RISIN' *

44:19.390 --> 44:22.861
* OOH, THERE HE IS
HE'S A KNOCKOUT MACHINE *

44:22.894 --> 44:24.863
* HE'S NUMBER ONE
HE'S DOUBLE COOL *
YEAH !

44:24.896 --> 44:27.465
* HE'S THE NAKED TRUTH
IN MAGAZINES *

44:27.498 --> 44:31.569
* I BELIEVE IN HIM
* WONDERMAN

44:31.602 --> 44:34.806
* HE IS A MR. WONDERMAN
* WONDERMAN

44:34.840 --> 44:36.875
* HE IS A MR. WONDERMAN

44:36.908 --> 44:39.811
* AH, YES

44:39.845 --> 44:44.515
* WONDERMAN
EW.

44:46.384 --> 44:51.389
* WONDERMAN
ONE MORE !
YES, YES, YES !

44:52.523 --> 44:54.860
AH !

45:00.866 --> 45:03.168
[ Preston ]
HEY, I'M GONNA GET YOU !

45:03.201 --> 45:06.571
[ Henry ]
YOU ARE LITTLE SUSHI MAN.
SUSHI MAN DOWN. BIG BOY THROW.

45:06.604 --> 45:09.574
THEN THEY CHASE AROUND.
COME AROUND OTHER WAY,
FALL DOWN. SPLAT.

45:09.607 --> 45:14.712
[ Preston Screaming ]
* HERE COMES THE WONDERMAN
HE'D LIKE TO SAY BYE-BYE **

45:17.816 --> 45:20.786
WHY ARE YOU DRESSED
LIKE A GAME SHOW HOST ?
I'M GOING OUT TONIGHT.

45:20.819 --> 45:22.888
JUST A MINUTE, YOUNG MAN.
YOU'RE STILL GROUNDED.

45:22.921 --> 45:26.624
BUT IT'S FOR MR. MACINTOSH.
I DON'T CARE.

45:26.657 --> 45:28.860
MACINTOSH MAY HAVE A PILE OF
MONEY, BUT HE DOESN'T DECIDE...

45:28.894 --> 45:30.896
WHEN MY SON
IS OR ISN'T GROUNDED.

45:30.929 --> 45:33.765
BUT IT'S FOR MY JOB.
YOUR JOB IS TO BE GROUNDED.

45:33.799 --> 45:38.904
- [ Both ] GROUNDED.
- SO MUCH FOR PLAN 442.

45:40.806 --> 45:43.875
WHAT DO YOU KNOW
ABOUT PLAN 442 ?

45:43.909 --> 45:47.946
WELL, IT'S THE INVESTMENT
PLAN YOU'VE BEEN WORKING ON,
YOUR "PRESPECTUS."

45:47.979 --> 45:52.483
PROSPECTUS.
WHAT ARE YOU DOING
GOING THROUGH MY WORK ?

45:52.517 --> 45:55.787
WELL, I DIDN'T WANT TO SAY IT,
BUT I TOLD MR. MACINTOSH...

45:55.821 --> 45:59.657
ABOUT YOUR PLAN 442, AND HE WAS
VERY, VERY INTERESTED.

45:59.690 --> 46:03.995
YEP, I PROMISED HIM I'D
BRING A COPY OF IT TONIGHT
AND SHOW IT TO HIM.

46:04.029 --> 46:07.665
BUT I DIDN'T WANT
TO TELL YOU JUST IN CASE YOU
GOT YOUR HOPES ALL UP AND--

46:07.698 --> 46:09.767
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO,
OF COURSE NOT.

46:09.801 --> 46:11.803
LET ME GET YOU A FRESH COPY
OF THE "PRESPECTUS."

46:11.837 --> 46:14.405
- I'LL GET A COPY
OF IT, SWEETHEART.
- PROSPECTUS.

46:14.439 --> 46:15.874
YEAH.

46:17.508 --> 46:19.945
HERE.
YOU'RE WELCOME.
OH, THANK YOU.

46:21.679 --> 46:23.815
HURRY UP. GO. GO !
YOU WANT THE CAR KEYS ?

46:23.849 --> 46:26.651
NAH, THAT'S OKAY, DAD.

46:26.684 --> 46:28.854
I DON'T DRIVE YET.

46:28.887 --> 46:31.456
[ Dad ] YOU WANT ME TO
DRIVE YOU ?
[ Preston ]
NO, IT'S OKAY.

46:31.489 --> 46:33.658
YOU KNOW, I STILL
HAVEN'T MET MACINTOSH.
MAYBE I SHOULD GO OVER AND--

46:33.691 --> 46:36.594
- NO ! YOU'LL RUIN EVERYTHING.
- WHY NOT ?

46:36.627 --> 46:39.430
HE HAS A DATE TONIGHT
AND HE'S VERY NERVOUS ABOUT IT.

46:39.464 --> 46:42.800
I GUESS I CAN SEE HIM
FIRST THING IN THE MORNING.
OH, I DON'T KNOW, DAD.

46:42.834 --> 46:46.938
I MEAN, HE MIGHT BE UP
PRETTY LATE WITH THIS WOMAN.

46:46.972 --> 46:51.509
[ Chuckles ]
LUCKY DOG.

46:55.713 --> 46:57.815
LATER, TOADS.

47:03.588 --> 47:06.457
[ Groaning ]
THANK YOU.
THAT'S ENOUGH.

47:06.491 --> 47:08.493
OH !
SORRY.

47:09.861 --> 47:13.531
I CAN'T BELIEVE
MR. MACINTOSH WENT
TO ALL THIS TROUBLE.

47:13.564 --> 47:18.403
THIS PLACE IS GREAT.
MR. MACINTOSH HAS BEEN
EATING HERE FOR YEARS.

47:18.436 --> 47:19.837
OH, YEAH ? I THOUGHT
HE JUST MOVED HERE.

47:19.871 --> 47:22.874
THERE WAS A TANGERINO
WHERE I USED TO LIVE.

47:22.908 --> 47:24.842
OH.

47:24.876 --> 47:27.378
[ Gargling ]

47:27.412 --> 47:31.682
COMPLIMENTS OF THE CHEF
FOR MR. WATERS...

47:31.716 --> 47:33.718
AND HIS LOVELY GUEST.

47:33.751 --> 47:38.423
TH-THEY LOOK
LIKE LOBSTERS,

47:38.456 --> 47:42.493
ONLY WEENIE.

47:42.527 --> 47:45.763
OH.

47:45.796 --> 47:48.833
MR. MACINTOSH WANTED YOU
TO HAVE THIS TOO.

47:48.866 --> 47:50.936
OH, THANKS.

47:52.537 --> 47:55.673
OH, WOW.

47:55.706 --> 47:58.944
THIS IS BEAUTIFUL. OH.

47:58.977 --> 48:02.447
BUT I CAN'T
ACCEPT THIS FROM YOU.

48:02.480 --> 48:05.416
BUT IT'S FROM MR. MACINTOSH.

48:05.450 --> 48:08.686
- WHY ?
- JUST A LITTLE BUSINESS GIFT.

48:08.719 --> 48:11.622
I MEAN, IT'S DEDUCTIBLE,
ISN'T IT ?

48:11.656 --> 48:15.961
I'M NOT REALLY SURE,
BUT IT'S WAY TOO EXPENSIVE.

48:15.994 --> 48:18.896
MR. MACINTOSH HAS
A MILLION DOLLARS.

48:18.930 --> 48:22.700
A MILLION DOLLARS DOESN'T BUY
ALL THAT MUCH THESE DAYS.

48:22.733 --> 48:24.869
DO YOU THINK HE SHOULD HAVE
ASKED FOR MORE ?

48:24.902 --> 48:28.806
WHAT EXACTLY
DOES HE DO ANYWAY ?

48:28.839 --> 48:31.609
OH, A LITTLE OF THIS,
A LITTLE OF THAT.

48:31.642 --> 48:34.545
YOU KNOW.
NO, I'M AFRAID I DON'T.

48:34.579 --> 48:37.815
- OH, WELL--
- IS HE AN ENTREPRENEUR ?

48:37.848 --> 48:42.387
NO, HE'S AMERICAN.
VERY SECRETIVE.

48:42.420 --> 48:44.489
HE HAS SOME QUESTIONS
FOR YOU TOO.

48:44.522 --> 48:47.592
OKAY.
SHOOT.

48:47.625 --> 48:50.895
"ARE YOU MARRIED ?"
NO.

48:50.928 --> 48:54.765
"WHAT'S THE SHORTEST GUY
YOU EVER DATED ?"

48:54.799 --> 48:57.969
MMM.
I'M NOT REALLY SURE.

48:58.003 --> 49:00.438
"THE YOUNGEST ?"
YOU KNOW,

49:00.471 --> 49:03.441
THESE ARE PRETTY
PERSONAL QUESTIONS.

49:03.474 --> 49:05.776
WELL, MR. MACINTOSH
IS VERY INTERESTED IN YOU.

49:05.810 --> 49:10.448
HE IS ?
HE'S, UH, NEVER MET
ANYBODY LIKE YOU BEFORE.

49:10.481 --> 49:13.651
HE'S NEVER MET ME BEFORE,
PERIOD.

49:13.684 --> 49:18.156
TECHNICALLY NO,
BUT HE'S BEEN THINKING
A LOT ABOUT YOU LATELY.

49:18.189 --> 49:24.162
- HE HAS ?
- YEP. WHOA !

49:24.195 --> 49:26.864
PRESTON !
ARE YOU OKAY ?

49:26.897 --> 49:31.169
- [ Screaming ]
- [ Gasps ]

49:31.202 --> 49:33.438
DO YOU LIKE HAMBURGERS ?

49:33.471 --> 49:36.374
I LOVE HAMBURGERS.

49:37.808 --> 49:40.845
NEVER SAW THIS KID
BEFORE IN MY LIFE.

49:40.878 --> 49:43.981
THIS IS A WASTE OF TIME.
COME ON.

49:44.015 --> 49:46.651
WHAT'S SO SPECIAL
ABOUT THIS PLACE ?

49:46.684 --> 49:50.655
YOU'LL SEE.
MMM, COME ON.
TELL ME.

49:50.688 --> 49:53.158
OKAY.
YOU GONNA TELL ME ?

49:53.191 --> 49:55.826
COME WITH ME.
ALL RIGHT.

49:59.864 --> 50:01.799
WHERE ARE YOU
TAKING ME ?
YOU'LL SEE.

50:01.832 --> 50:04.169
SEE WHAT ?
OKAY,
GET IN THE MIDDLE.

50:04.202 --> 50:09.907
OKAY, READY ?
FIVE, FOUR, THREE,
HERE ?

50:09.940 --> 50:12.910
TWO, ONE.

50:12.943 --> 50:15.846
[ Shay Laughing ]
HOLY SMOKES !

50:15.880 --> 50:18.649
OKAY ! OKAY, NOW,
COME HERE, SHAY !

50:18.683 --> 50:20.651
OKAY, OKAY, NOW !
PRESTON,
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS !

50:20.685 --> 50:23.554
OKAY, NOW,
LET'S RUN AROUND !

50:23.588 --> 50:27.425
DON'T GET WET !
GET US OUT !

50:27.458 --> 50:29.560
RUN !
[ Screams ]

50:29.594 --> 50:32.430
OKAY, OKAY, OKAY !
WATCH OUT !

50:32.463 --> 50:34.732
- NO, WE'RE GONNA GET SOAKED !
- NO, NO, NO. NOW COME--

50:34.765 --> 50:37.468
COME AROUND HERE !
COME AROUND HERE !
COME ON !

50:42.707 --> 50:45.776
OKAY, HOLD ONTO ME.
[ Screaming ]
HEY, WHERE ARE YOU ?

50:45.810 --> 50:49.480
[ Screaming ]
YEAH ! YES !

50:51.716 --> 50:54.785
WHOO, YEAH !
PRESTON !

51:16.807 --> 51:20.711
[ Clapping, Cheering ]

51:20.745 --> 51:23.581
THIS IS A GREAT IDEA, BIDERMAN.
WHERE'S ALL THE KIDS, HUH ?

51:23.614 --> 51:26.484
CARL,
IT'S LATE AT NIGHT.

51:26.517 --> 51:28.119
ALL THE LITTLE BOYS AND GIRLS
ARE TUCKED IN BED.
WHAT DO YOU EXPECT ?

51:28.153 --> 51:32.590
WHAT I EXPECT IS WHEN I GIVE
SOMEONE A MILLION DOLLARS,
AND I COME BACK A DAY LATER,

51:32.623 --> 51:34.592
I FIND THE MILLION DOLLARS.
THAT'S WHAT I EXPECT.

51:34.625 --> 51:37.595
CARL, I'M NOT
A MAGICIAN.
YOU CAN MAKE IT
DISAPPEAR,

51:37.628 --> 51:40.431
YOU JUST CAN'T
GET IT BACK, RIGHT ?
I'M TELLING YOU--

51:40.465 --> 51:41.799
IF Y'ALL WANT A KID SO BAD,
THERE GO ONE OVER THERE.

51:41.832 --> 51:44.835
[ Biderman ]
THAT'S THE LITTLE BOY
FROM THE BANK !

51:47.605 --> 51:50.675
SHH.

51:50.708 --> 51:53.378
SHH.

51:54.845 --> 51:57.448
- [ Preston Screams ]
- GO GET HIM !

51:57.482 --> 52:00.151
OH, I'LL RACE YA TO THE LIMO !
I'LL RACE YA TO THE LIMO !
WHAT ? OKAY, I'LL RACE YA !

52:00.185 --> 52:03.954
[ Shouting ]

52:03.988 --> 52:06.457
[ Screaming ]

52:06.491 --> 52:08.859
I GOT THE DOOR FOR YA !
OPEN THE DOOR.
IT'S FREEZING !

52:08.893 --> 52:11.862
GO, HENRY !
GO, HENRY, GO !

52:11.896 --> 52:16.000
- [ Henry ] HERE WE GO !
- [ Groaning ]

52:16.033 --> 52:20.571
HE GOT AWAY AGAIN !
I DON'T BELIEVE THIS !
HE GOT AWAY AGAIN !

52:21.672 --> 52:24.509
[ Screaming ]

52:24.542 --> 52:27.645
[ Shay ]
THIS WAS THE MOST FUN.

52:27.678 --> 52:32.149
I HAVEN'T DONE ANYTHING LIKE
THIS SINCE I WAS A LITTLE KID.
ME NEITHER.

52:32.183 --> 52:34.552
THANK YOU SO MUCH.

52:34.585 --> 52:36.787
WHEN CAN I
SEE YOU AGAIN ?

52:36.821 --> 52:42.693
WELL, I REALLY HAVE
TO SPEND SOME TIME
WITH MY JOB RIGHT NOW.

52:43.894 --> 52:47.465
WELL, UH,
I'M HAVING A PARTY.

52:47.498 --> 52:49.467
ON FRIDAY.

52:49.500 --> 52:51.502
CAN YOU COME ?

52:51.536 --> 52:53.638
IT'S FOR MR. MACINTOSH.

52:53.671 --> 52:57.642
UM, IT COULD BE
FOR YOUR BUSINESS, SORT OF.

52:57.675 --> 53:00.177
MR. MACINTOSH WILL
REALLY BE THERE ?

53:00.211 --> 53:03.648
UH-HUH.
IT'S HIS BIRTHDAY.

53:03.681 --> 53:06.417
OKAY.
WELL, GREAT.

53:06.451 --> 53:08.419
IT'S A DATE THEN.

53:08.453 --> 53:10.588
OH, I'M GETTING OUT
UP HERE.

53:14.759 --> 53:17.562
IT WAS REALLY FUN.

53:17.595 --> 53:19.697
AND, UH,

53:19.730 --> 53:23.901
I HAD SUCH
A GOOD TIME.
ME TOO.

53:23.934 --> 53:28.373
GOOD NIGHT, PRESTON.
GOOD NIGHT, SHAY.

53:30.808 --> 53:33.911
SEE YOU LATER.
BYE-BYE.

53:36.614 --> 53:39.650
GOOD NIGHT, MA'AM. BYE NOW.
IT'S BEEN A PLEASURE.
THANK YOU.

53:57.468 --> 53:59.604
[ Henry ]
SO YOU'RE HAVING
A PARTY FRIDAY ?

53:59.637 --> 54:02.407
[ Preston ]
OH, YEAH, IT'S
MR. MACINTOSH'S BIRTHDAY.

54:02.440 --> 54:04.141
OH, I THOUGHT YOU SAID
IT WAS YOUR BIRTHDAY FRIDAY.

54:04.174 --> 54:06.877
WELL, WE'RE GONNA HAVE
A JOINT PARTY FOR
THE BOTH OF US.

54:06.911 --> 54:10.581
OH. WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING
IT WORKED OUT YOUR BIRTHDAYS
ARE AROUND THE SAME TIME.

54:10.615 --> 54:14.852
HEY, YOU WANNA MOVE THAT HORSE ?
COME ON. WHAT IS THIS,
BONANZA ? LET'S GO !

54:16.621 --> 54:18.889
WELL, HERE WE ARE.
HOME AT LAST.

54:18.923 --> 54:21.459
THANKS, HENRY.
MY PLEASURE.

54:21.492 --> 54:23.494
HEY !
PRESTON WATERS !

54:23.528 --> 54:25.663
GOOD NIGHT.
YOU KNOW WHAT
YOU GOT, PAL ?

54:25.696 --> 54:28.833
WHAT ?
S-T-Y-L-E.

54:28.866 --> 54:32.603
STYLE.
GOOD NIGHT, HENRY.
STYLE. GOOD NIGHT.

54:33.938 --> 54:36.774
TAKE IT EASY, MAN.
GOOD NIGHT.

54:39.610 --> 54:44.882
MACINTOSH AND I ARE HAVING
THE BIGGEST BIRTHDAY PARTY EVER.

55:03.701 --> 55:07.472
HONEY, WHERE'S PRESTON ?
HE'S WORKING
FOR MACINTOSH.

55:07.505 --> 55:10.841
OH. WHERE'S
DAMIEN AND RALPH ?

55:10.875 --> 55:13.444
THEY'RE WORKING
FOR MACINTOSH TOO.

55:13.478 --> 55:15.680
OH.

55:20.885 --> 55:24.154
- HAVE YOU MET MACINTOSH ?
- NO, I THOUGHT YOU MET HIM.

55:24.188 --> 55:27.658
NO, I HAVEN'T MET HIM.
WELL, I HAVEN'T
MET HIM EITHER.

55:27.692 --> 55:29.727
[ Machine Humming ]

55:32.697 --> 55:38.603
KEEP 'EM COMIN'.
MR. MACINTOSH WANTS ME
TO GET PLENTY OF PRACTICE.

55:40.705 --> 55:43.808
[ Screams ]
WATCH WHERE YOU'RE
HITTIN' THOSE !

55:43.841 --> 55:46.544
QUIT MESSIN' AROUND.
MACINTOSH IS WATCHING.

55:46.577 --> 55:48.713
WHERE ? WE'VE STILL
NEVER SEEN HIM.

55:48.746 --> 55:51.416
JUST GET BACK TO WORK.
HE'S WATCHING.

55:52.883 --> 55:55.553
** [ Loud Rock ]
[ Man ] ...COMING
OUT OF THE GARAGE.

55:55.586 --> 55:57.555
RUINING THE NEIGHBORHOOD.

55:57.588 --> 56:00.558
** [ Continues ]

56:00.591 --> 56:02.927
[ Shooting Noises ]

56:02.960 --> 56:05.763
[ Henry ]
HEY, PRESTON !

56:05.796 --> 56:07.765
YOUR PARTY PLANNER'S
HERE AGAIN.

56:07.798 --> 56:10.568
[ Woman ]
PISTON ! PISTON ! PISTON !

56:10.601 --> 56:12.670
TURN OFF THIS CONTRAPTION.
I HAVE WONDERFUL NEWS.

56:12.703 --> 56:16.874
MR. MACINTOSH'S BIRTHDAY
IS GOING TO BE THE EVENT
OF THE CENTURY.

56:16.907 --> 56:18.909
WE GONNA MAKE
THE FRONT PAGE FROM
COAST TO COAST.

56:18.943 --> 56:21.446
OH, WE ARE SO LUCKY,
LUCKY, LUCKY !

56:21.479 --> 56:23.848
NOW WHAT KIND OF FOOD
DOES MR. MACINTOSH LIKE ?

56:23.881 --> 56:25.783
I DON'T KNOW.
AND WHO ARE
HIS FRIENDS ?

56:25.816 --> 56:30.855
- DO YOU HAVE A GUEST LIST ?
- UH, I DON'T THINK SO.

56:30.888 --> 56:33.357
YOU KNOW, DEWDROP, I THINK
I SHOULD MEET HIM BECAUSE...

56:33.390 --> 56:35.392
I'M GONNA NEED
A LITTLE CASH DEPOSIT.

56:35.426 --> 56:38.796
OH. UH, HERE.
LET ME GET YOU SOME CASH.

56:38.829 --> 56:40.965
OOH, YES, YOU DO
HAVE MONEY, DON'T YOU ?

56:40.998 --> 56:44.435
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
CAREFUL WALKING AROUND WITH
THIS MUCH MONEY, DARLING.

56:44.469 --> 56:46.437
SOMEBODY COULD JUST
RIP YOU RIGHT OFF.

56:46.471 --> 56:49.440
NOW, THIS FIRST $10,000
IS GOING TO BE THE DEPOSIT.

56:49.474 --> 56:51.709
NOW, OF COURSE, I'LL GET
THE BALANCE AT THE PARTY,

56:51.742 --> 56:55.646
AND MR. MACINTOSH
IS GOOD FOR IT ?

56:55.680 --> 56:58.649
I AM JUST SO LOOKING FORWARD
TO MEETING HIM.

56:58.683 --> 57:01.719
- WHO ISN'T ?
- WAITERS, SECURITY,

57:01.752 --> 57:03.921
GUEST LIST,
PAPARAZZI--
OH, AND YVONNE ?

57:03.954 --> 57:07.792
YES ?
REMEMBER,
IT'S PRESTON.

57:07.825 --> 57:09.694
WHATEVER !

57:12.196 --> 57:14.431
HEY, UH, HEY, HENRY.

57:14.465 --> 57:19.937
[ Grunting, Laughing ]
IT'S ATTACK OF THE 50-FOOT
CHAUFFEUR FROM HELL !

57:19.970 --> 57:23.674
I WAS JUST WONDERING IF YOU
WANTED TO PLAY SOME VIDEO GAMES.

57:23.708 --> 57:25.676
OH, MAN, I WISH YOU'D
HAVE SAID SOMETHING.

57:25.710 --> 57:28.445
I CAN'T. I PROMISED
SOME FRIENDS I WAS GONNA
MEET 'EM IN A WHILE.

57:28.479 --> 57:31.415
OH, OKAY.
NO PROBLEM.

57:31.448 --> 57:33.450
I'LL TELL YOU WHAT.
I'LL DROP YOU OVER AT ONE
OF YOUR FRIEND'S PLACE...

57:33.484 --> 57:35.586
ON THE WAY OVER, AND YOU
CAN HAVE SOME FUN THERE.

57:35.620 --> 57:39.624
NAH.
MAYBE I'LL GO TO THE PARK.

57:39.657 --> 57:41.759
ALL RIGHT.
IT'S UP TO YOU.
HEY, PRESTON,

57:41.792 --> 57:45.162
IS MY TIE
STRAIGHT ?
WELL, IT LOOKS PERFECT.

57:45.195 --> 57:48.365
ALL RIGHT.
LATER.

58:17.161 --> 58:20.865
OVER HERE.
OVER HERE !

58:40.851 --> 58:44.488
THERE IT IS.
THAT'S THE PARK UP AHEAD.

58:44.521 --> 58:47.825
WHERE DID ALL THESE KIDS
COME FROM ?

58:47.858 --> 58:50.360
KEEP DRIVING AND MAYBE
SOMEDAY I'LL TELL YOU.

58:50.394 --> 58:54.732
- HOW COULD YOU HIT A KID ?
- I DIDN'T HIT A KID.
I RAN OVER HIS BICYCLE.

58:54.765 --> 58:57.568
I HAD A DOG ONCE
THAT GOT HIT BY A TRAIN.

58:57.602 --> 59:00.905
THANKS FOR SHARING,
JUICE.
OLD KING COLE
WE CALLED HIM.

59:00.938 --> 59:03.674
HE WAS A MERRY
OLD SOUL.
IT'S HIM.

59:03.708 --> 59:06.543
BOY WITH THE BACKPACK.
GO ! GO ! GO !

59:06.577 --> 59:09.413
THE SIGN SAYS
"NO CARS ALLOWED" !
JUST DRIVE !

59:09.446 --> 59:12.583
QUIGLEY !

59:12.617 --> 59:16.186
YOU'RE GONNA
PAY FOR THIS !
JUST DRIVE !

59:16.220 --> 59:19.523
CARL, THIS
ISN'T A GOOD IDEA.
SHUT UP ! WHOA !

59:19.556 --> 59:23.327
LET GO, MAN.
WHAT'S GOIN' ON ?

59:23.894 --> 59:26.697
OOOH !
OOOH !

59:26.731 --> 59:29.700
I'M GONNA GET HIM.
WE'RE GONNA
TEAR HIM UP !

59:29.734 --> 59:33.704
REACH OVER THERE
AND GET HIM !
YOUR BUTT IS MINE, KID !

59:33.738 --> 59:35.640
I'VE BEEN WANTIN'
THIS LITTLE PUNK.

59:35.673 --> 59:38.809
I OWN YOU !
I OWN YOU, KID !

59:38.843 --> 59:43.814
COME HERE !
HE'S GOT MY MONEY !

59:43.848 --> 59:46.350
AAAAH !

59:49.186 --> 59:51.488
FOLLOW HIM ON FOOT !
GO !
FOLLOW HIM ON FOOT ?

59:51.521 --> 59:54.491
DO I LOOK LIKE A BLOODHOUND,
A PROFESSIONAL TRACKER ?
JUICY, LISTEN.

59:54.524 --> 59:57.461
IF WE DON'T GET THAT KID,
NOBODY GETS PAID.

59:57.494 --> 59:59.664
[ Groaning ]

59:59.697 --> 01:00:04.568
I WANT CASH BENEFITS,
DENTAL, EVERYTHING.
NOT A PROBLEM.

01:00:04.601 --> 01:00:08.472
INSURANCE !
HERE, KIDDIE, KIDDIE !

01:00:08.505 --> 01:00:11.942
OH, THERE YOU GO.
COME HERE, BOY.
I'M GONNA GET YOU NOW.

01:00:11.976 --> 01:00:15.545
I'VE BEEN LOOKIN' FOR YOU !

01:00:16.714 --> 01:00:19.717
HUH ? OH, NO.

01:00:21.719 --> 01:00:24.689
THERE HE GOES.
YES. COME HERE, BOY !

01:00:24.722 --> 01:00:27.624
I'M GONNA GET YOU NOW !
AAAAH !

01:00:30.527 --> 01:00:35.966
DON'T BELIEVE THIS !
KILL THAT KID WHEN I FIND HIM.
I'M NOT GETTIN' PAID FOR THIS.

01:00:36.000 --> 01:00:39.503
WHERE ARE WE GOING NOW ?
MY HANDS ARE OVER MY EYES.
SHUT UP !

01:00:43.373 --> 01:00:45.710
- GET OUT--
- [ Screaming ]

01:00:47.011 --> 01:00:50.380
THERE HE IS !
STICK WITH IT !
I GOT YA !

01:00:50.414 --> 01:00:52.683
[ Juice ]
I'LL GET YOU !

01:00:52.717 --> 01:00:55.820
HANG ON, HANG ON.

01:00:55.853 --> 01:00:58.856
OKAY, THERE HE IS !
COME HERE !
COME HERE !

01:00:58.889 --> 01:01:01.558
JUICE ! RUN AFTER HIM.
YOU MUST BE CRAZY.
YOU RUN AFTER HIM.

01:01:01.591 --> 01:01:05.696
JUST RAN THROUGH
THIS WHOLE ENTIRE PARK.
FINE, GET IN THE CAR.

01:01:05.730 --> 01:01:08.999
[ Coughing ]
DON'T BLOW CHUNKS IN MY CAR.
I JUST HAD IT DETAILED.

01:01:09.033 --> 01:01:12.569
I'M COOL !
ARE YOU SURE ?
ARE YOU SURE ?

01:01:12.602 --> 01:01:15.873
I'M NOT GONNA MESS UP
YOUR PRICELESS DETAIL.
COME ON.

01:01:15.906 --> 01:01:18.375
[ Retching ]
HEY !

01:01:20.610 --> 01:01:23.714
[ Boy ]
WOW, WHAT'S THIS ?

01:01:24.915 --> 01:01:27.718
LET'S GO !
AFTER HIM !

01:01:29.419 --> 01:01:31.756
- HEY, DUDE !
- [ Juice ] MOVE OUTTA THE WAY.

01:01:31.789 --> 01:01:33.924
SORRY !

01:01:41.465 --> 01:01:46.370
GET 'IM !
YOUR BUTT IS MINE !

01:01:49.740 --> 01:01:51.742
I WANT THIS KID--
WHAT ARE YOU DOING ?

01:01:51.776 --> 01:01:55.379
- YEAH !
- NO ! CARL, WATCH OUT !

01:01:55.412 --> 01:01:57.748
[ Juice ]
OH, NO !

01:01:57.782 --> 01:02:00.484
WHOA !

01:02:04.889 --> 01:02:08.759
AAH ! NO !
OH, MAN !

01:02:08.793 --> 01:02:11.728
YES !

01:02:11.762 --> 01:02:14.865
NOW THAT'S A DISPLAY
OF FINE DRIVING RIGHT THERE.

01:02:14.899 --> 01:02:19.736
YOU KNOW, CARL, IT MIGHT
BE EASIER JUST TO STEAL
ANOTHER MILLION DOLLARS.

01:02:27.912 --> 01:02:31.816
HELLO, MR. JACKSON.

01:02:31.849 --> 01:02:36.653
WELL, WELL, WELL, IF IT
ISN'T THE WORLD'S YOUNGEST
PERSONAL INJURY ATTORNEY.

01:02:36.686 --> 01:02:39.656
YOU KNOW, YOU'RE IN A LOT
OF TROUBLE TODAY, LITTLE MAN.

01:02:39.689 --> 01:02:42.159
YEAH, 'CAUSE TODAY
I HAVE BEEN DRINKING VODKA.

01:02:42.192 --> 01:02:44.829
- TAKE A HIKE, BUTT-BRAIN.
- WHAT ?

01:02:44.862 --> 01:02:48.665
TAKE A--
NEVER MIND, NEVER MIND.
NEVER MIND, NEVER MIND !

01:02:48.698 --> 01:02:51.635
[ Chattering ]

01:02:51.668 --> 01:02:54.805
[ Yvonne ]
ANTOINE, GET THAT TRUCK THING
OFF THE STAGE. THANK YOU !

01:02:56.841 --> 01:03:00.510
GET THOSE GOLDEN GLOVES OFF !
THANK YOU !

01:03:02.612 --> 01:03:05.682
LOVE, LOVE, LOVE, LOVE !
WHAT DO YOU THINK ?

01:03:05.715 --> 01:03:08.819
TA-DA ! IS THIS
TO DIE, OR WHAT ?

01:03:08.853 --> 01:03:11.922
UH, YEAH, SURE,
IT'S, UH, TO DIE.

01:03:11.956 --> 01:03:14.825
I CAN'T WAIT TO SHOW IT
TO MR. MACINTOSH.

01:03:14.859 --> 01:03:16.994
COME ON, HONEY, LET'S SEE
WHAT THEY DID WITH THAT--

01:03:17.027 --> 01:03:21.365
"IS IT TO DIE FOR OR WHAT ?"
[ Laughing ]

01:03:21.398 --> 01:03:25.502
WHERE DID YOU FIND HER ?
OH, MAN.

01:03:25.535 --> 01:03:28.873
WHAT DOES
THIS COST ?
I DON'T KNOW.

01:03:28.906 --> 01:03:33.878
WHAT DO YOU THINK
IT SHOULD COST ?
LOTS, LOTS.

01:03:33.911 --> 01:03:36.613
KID, WHY DON'T YOU JUST
TELL ME WHAT I NEED TO KNOW.
I'M A GOOD GUY.

01:03:36.646 --> 01:03:40.584
OKAY, HOW GOOD ARE YOU
GOING TO BE TO ME ?
IN ROUND NUMBERS.

01:03:41.718 --> 01:03:44.855
I DON'T THINK YOU GET
THE PICTURE, SONNY.

01:03:47.724 --> 01:03:50.827
MAYBE YOU NEED
A BETTER VIEW.
[ Screaming ]

01:03:50.861 --> 01:03:54.364
[ Screaming ]
PRESTON WATERS, 1508 OAK STREET,
HILLSDALE, INDIANA !

01:03:54.398 --> 01:03:57.801
- THANK YOU.
- [ Crying ]

01:03:57.834 --> 01:03:59.836
YOU ALL RIGHT ?
AAAH ! AAAH !

01:03:59.870 --> 01:04:03.507
IS SOMETHING WRONG ?
NO, NOT AT ALL.

01:04:03.540 --> 01:04:07.677
- IS MR. MACINTOSH AROUND ?
- UH, NO.

01:04:07.711 --> 01:04:09.713
- BUT HE WILL BE HERE TONIGHT ?
- YEAH.

01:04:09.746 --> 01:04:11.715
IN PERSON ?
IN PERSON.

01:04:11.748 --> 01:04:14.919
OKAY. I'LL SEE
YOU TONIGHT ?
OKAY.

01:04:14.952 --> 01:04:18.655
OKAY. YOU'RE
LOOKING GOOD. BYE.

01:04:18.688 --> 01:04:22.559
I'LL BE CALLING.
WHAT A BABE.

01:04:22.592 --> 01:04:24.561
BABY BROTHER
COMES INTO HIS OWN.

01:04:24.594 --> 01:04:26.563
FOR A LITTLE WEASEL,
HE SURE KNOWS HOW
TO GET A GIRLFRIEND.

01:04:26.596 --> 01:04:29.166
TOO BAD HE PICKED
A FORTUNE HUNTER.
LITTLE LOVE PILOT...

01:04:29.199 --> 01:04:31.701
SHOT DOWN IN FLAMES
BY A GOLD DIGGER.

01:04:31.735 --> 01:04:33.737
BY A WHAT ?

01:04:33.770 --> 01:04:37.374
GOLD DIGGER, SOMEONE
WHO IS ONLY AFTER MONEY.
I KNOW WOMEN,

01:04:37.407 --> 01:04:39.843
AND THAT ONE IS AFTER
MACINTOSH'S COLD, HARD CASH.

01:04:39.876 --> 01:04:44.681
FOR YOUR INFORMATION,
ME AND SHAY ALREADY
WENT ON A DATE...

01:04:44.714 --> 01:04:47.851
AND SHE HAD ONE
FANTASTIC TIME, BOYS.

01:04:47.884 --> 01:04:51.421
OH, YES, EVERY SECOND
SHE WAS GETTING CLOSER...

01:04:51.455 --> 01:04:53.690
AND CLOSER
TO MR. MACINTOSH.
[ Laughing ]

01:04:53.723 --> 01:04:57.561
SHUT UP !
JUST ANSWER ME THIS.

01:04:57.594 --> 01:05:00.764
DID SHE EVER,
EVER JUST ONCE,
COME BY WITHOUT SAYING,

01:05:00.797 --> 01:05:03.934
"MEANWHILE, I WONDER IF
I COULD SEE MR. MACINTOSH ?"

01:05:03.968 --> 01:05:06.903
SHE'S A GOLD DIGGER, MAN.
SHE JUST WANTS
MACINTOSH'S MONEY.

01:05:06.937 --> 01:05:09.606
YEAH !
OW !
DON'T RUB IT.
BE A MAN.

01:05:09.639 --> 01:05:12.142
DON'T RUB IT.
I'LL RUB IT
IF I WANT TO.

01:05:12.176 --> 01:05:16.846
SHE WANTS A GUY WITH MONEY,
NOT SOME LITTLE KID WITH
AN EMPTY PIGGY BANK.
YEAH.

01:05:36.500 --> 01:05:41.471
* WELL, I'LL WAIT BY THE WINDOWS
I'LL WAIT BY THE DOOR *

01:05:41.505 --> 01:05:43.640
* TO MAKE SURE
YOU DON'T COME HOME **

01:05:43.673 --> 01:05:48.578
YOU EVER KNOWN
ANY GOLD DIGGERS ?
MAN, HAVE I.

01:05:48.612 --> 01:05:50.747
I HATE 'EM.
THEY'RE THE WORST.

01:05:50.780 --> 01:05:55.952
ANYBODY WHO IS YOUR FRIEND
BECAUSE YOU HAVE MONEY
IS NOT YOUR FRIEND AT ALL.

01:05:55.986 --> 01:05:58.488
YOU KNOW WHAT
THEY SAY ABOUT GOLD ?

01:05:58.522 --> 01:06:01.491
"HE WHO HAS THE GOLD
MAKES THE RULES" ?

01:06:01.525 --> 01:06:04.861
NO, NO, NO.
"A FOOL AND HIS GOLD
ARE SOON PARTED."

01:06:04.894 --> 01:06:06.830
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN ?

01:06:06.863 --> 01:06:10.367
"A FOOL AND HIS GOLD
ARE SOON PARTED."
THOSE OLD SAYINGS, MAN,

01:06:10.400 --> 01:06:12.869
I DON'T GET 'EM. I DON'T EVEN
KNOW REALLY WHAT THAT MEANS.

01:06:12.902 --> 01:06:16.840
YOU EVER HEARD:
"MORE THAN ONE WAY
TO SKIN A CAT" ?

01:06:16.873 --> 01:06:19.509
WHO SKINS CATS ?
WHY WOULD YOU SKIN A CAT ?

01:06:19.543 --> 01:06:23.347
AND THERE IS NOT MORE THAN
ONE WAY TO SKIN A CAT.
THERE IS ONLY ONE WAY.

01:06:23.380 --> 01:06:25.449
YOU GRAB THE CAT,
YOU RIP THE SKIN OFF THE CAT.

01:06:25.482 --> 01:06:27.951
WHAT IS THE NUMBER TWO WAY ?
YOU PUT A HOSE
UP THE CAT'S BUTT ?

01:06:27.984 --> 01:06:29.986
HE GETS SO BLOATED
THAT HE SKINS HIMSELF ?

01:06:30.020 --> 01:06:34.658
DOES HE HAVE A PIECE
OF VELCRO UNDER HIS BUTT ? NO.

01:06:34.691 --> 01:06:37.894
"KILL TWO BIRDS WITH ONE STONE."
YOU HEARD THAT ONE ?

01:06:37.927 --> 01:06:40.697
YOU KNOW ANYONE WHO HAS EVEN
KILLED ONE BIRD WITH ONE STONE ?

01:06:40.730 --> 01:06:42.832
KIDS TRY IT ALL THE TIME.
YOU CAN'T HIT A BIRD
WITH A STONE.

01:06:42.866 --> 01:06:45.702
UNLESS YOU GOT A HUGE STONE
AND THEY'RE TINY BABY BIRDS.

01:06:45.735 --> 01:06:49.673
THEN-- [ Imitating Crash ]
BEEP, BEEP ! DEAD.

01:06:49.706 --> 01:06:52.842
[ Sighing ]
"A FOOL AND HIS GOLD
ARE SOON PARTED."

01:06:52.876 --> 01:06:56.480
I GUESS IT MEANS
THAT IF YOU'RE A FOOL,

01:06:56.513 --> 01:06:58.582
YOUR GOLD OR YOUR MONEY
IS SOON GONE.

01:06:58.615 --> 01:07:01.418
ONCE IT'S GONE, IT IS
OUTTA THERE. IT IS HISTORY.

01:07:01.451 --> 01:07:05.155
IT IS DUST.
IT IS VAPOR. IT IS NO MORE.
YOU ARE LIVING IN BROKESVILLE.

01:07:05.189 --> 01:07:09.559
UNLESS YOU HAVE
MACINTOSH'S KIND OF MONEY.
WHAT IF YOU DON'T ?

01:07:09.593 --> 01:07:13.930
I GUESS THEN YOU FIND OUT
WHO YOUR REAL FRIENDS ARE.

01:07:15.599 --> 01:07:18.402
MAN, WE LOOK GOOD.

01:07:25.742 --> 01:07:29.546
IS EVERYBODY
HAVING A GOOD TIME ?
[ Woman Laughing ]

01:07:29.579 --> 01:07:32.382
GOOD, YOU ARE.
"YES, WE ARE, DARLING."
WOW, LOOK AT THE BALLOONS.

01:07:32.416 --> 01:07:36.586
THIS IS GREAT.
LOOK AT THE ICE SCULPTURE.
PRESENTS !

01:07:36.620 --> 01:07:40.790
HEY, HEY, HEY, KID,
NO TOUCHING.
THOSE ARE MR. MACINTOSH'S.

01:07:40.824 --> 01:07:45.562
GO FIND YOUR PARENTS.
GO ON, GET OUTTA HERE.

01:07:45.595 --> 01:07:48.798
GO ON !

01:07:48.832 --> 01:07:52.369
I JUST WANT TO SEE
MR. MACINTOSH.
I JUST WANT TO PIG OUT.

01:07:52.402 --> 01:07:54.938
[ Chuckling ]
HEY, LOOK AT THAT.

01:07:54.971 --> 01:07:57.341
EXCUSE ME.

01:07:58.842 --> 01:08:03.647
SORRY !
EXACTLY WHO ARE YOU
LOOKING FOR, PRESTON ?

01:08:03.680 --> 01:08:07.484
HAVE YOU SEEN SHAY ?
I HAVEN'T SEEN HER,
BUT SHE'LL BE AROUND.

01:08:07.517 --> 01:08:10.387
COME ON-- OH, MAN,
LOOK AT ALL THIS FOOD !

01:08:10.420 --> 01:08:12.489
MACINTOSH DOESN'T SHOW,
WE BRING THE KID IN,
AGREED ?

01:08:12.522 --> 01:08:17.394
IF PRESTON SAYS
MACINTOSH IS GONNA BE THERE,
MACINTOSH WILL BE THERE.

01:08:17.426 --> 01:08:21.430
BUT YOU DON'T MAKE A MOVE,
UNTIL I GIVE YOU THE SIGNAL,
UNDERSTOOD ?

01:08:21.465 --> 01:08:24.468
WE GOT EIGHT MEN READY
TO GO IN AND NAIL HIM
THE SECOND HE SHOWS UP !

01:08:24.501 --> 01:08:27.470
WE CLOSE THIS DEAL TONIGHT !

01:08:30.607 --> 01:08:34.678
WHERE'S THE PIZZA
AND THE ICE CREAM ?
WHAT'S GOING ON HERE ?

01:08:34.711 --> 01:08:38.348
THIS COULD HAVE BEEN
A PIZZA BEFORE IT GOT RUN OVER
BY A COUPLE OF TRUCKS.

01:08:38.381 --> 01:08:42.452
OH, THAT LOOKS TASTY.
LOOKS LIKE SOMETHING
YOU'D FIND BETWEEN YOUR TOES.

01:08:42.486 --> 01:08:46.689
AH, AH, AH !
IT'S SUCKING THE LIFE OUTTA ME !

01:08:46.723 --> 01:08:50.660
- SHUT UP !
EVERYBODY'S LOOKING.
- SO WHAT ? WHO CARES ?

01:08:50.694 --> 01:08:53.930
RELAX, HAVE A GOOD TIME.
SHE'LL SHOW UP.
OH, THERE'S SHAY NOW. HA !

01:08:53.962 --> 01:08:57.367
JUST KIDDING.
I WAS KIDDING YA !
WOULD YOU JUST RELAX ?

01:08:57.401 --> 01:09:01.938
SHE'LL BE HERE.
IT'S NOT AT ALL WHAT
YOU THOUGHT IT'D BE LIKE ?

01:09:01.970 --> 01:09:07.711
HATE BEING RICH, HUH ?
PRESTON ? PRESTON ?

01:09:11.415 --> 01:09:13.350
ICE CREAM, ICE CREAM.

01:09:13.383 --> 01:09:16.486
YOO-HOO, PRESTON !

01:09:16.520 --> 01:09:19.622
NOW, WHERE IS OUR MYSTERY MAN ?
IT'S TIME FOR MR. MACINTOSH
TO MAKE HIS APPEARANCE.

01:09:19.656 --> 01:09:22.859
I LIKE TO GIVE MY EMPLOYERS
THEIR BILLS DIRECTLY.

01:09:22.892 --> 01:09:26.895
THAT WAY IF THEY HAVE ANY
QUESTIONS OR HEART ATTACKS
OR SOMETHING--

01:09:26.930 --> 01:09:30.567
I'LL GIVE IT TO HIM.
FINE.

01:09:30.600 --> 01:09:33.670
BE QUICK ABOUT IT.

01:09:33.703 --> 01:09:36.805
$100,000 ?

01:09:36.840 --> 01:09:40.810
SWEETHEART, I KNOW THIS SEEMS
LIKE A WHOLE LOT OF MONEY TO
NORMAL PEOPLE LIKE ME AND YOU,

01:09:40.844 --> 01:09:43.479
BUT TO A MAN LIKE MACINTOSH
THIS IS JUST PENNIES.

01:09:43.513 --> 01:09:46.683
NOW, YOU GET UP THERE
AND GET ME MY MONEY !
OW ! I'LL GET YOUR MONEY.

01:09:46.716 --> 01:09:49.853
[ Computer Beeping ]

01:09:54.891 --> 01:09:59.596
PARTY: $100,000.

01:09:59.629 --> 01:10:01.898
NOT A PROBLEM.
YOU CAN LEAVE IT.

01:10:01.931 --> 01:10:03.700
THIS IS FINE.
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.
THANK YOU.

01:10:03.733 --> 01:10:06.836
[ Computer ]
TRANSACTION NOT POSSIBLE.

01:10:06.870 --> 01:10:09.373
INSUFFICIENT FUNDS.

01:10:09.406 --> 01:10:13.743
CURRENT BALANCE: $332.17.

01:10:13.777 --> 01:10:16.513
TRANSACTION NOT POSSIBLE.
THREE HUNDRED DOLLARS ?

01:10:16.546 --> 01:10:19.849
INSUFFICIENT FUNDS.
TRANSACTION NOT POSSIBLE.
OH, NO !

01:10:19.883 --> 01:10:22.786
NO, PLEASE, GOD.
INSUFFICIENT FUNDS.

01:10:22.819 --> 01:10:26.690
THIS CAN'T BE RIGHT.

01:10:26.723 --> 01:10:31.895
ONE, TWO, THREE, FOUR--

01:10:35.399 --> 01:10:38.368
[ Chattering ]

01:10:38.402 --> 01:10:41.638
IT'S GONE.
IT'S ALL GONE.

01:10:41.671 --> 01:10:44.441
[ Knocking ]

01:10:44.474 --> 01:10:46.576
MR. MACINTOSH ?
OH, SORRY TO BOTHER YOU.

01:10:46.610 --> 01:10:49.713
IT'S FRED WATERS,
PRESTON'S DAD.

01:10:49.746 --> 01:10:52.782
I KNOW YOU GOT
A BASH GOING ON HERE,
SO I'LL MAKE IT BRIEF.

01:10:52.816 --> 01:10:54.784
BUT, UH,

01:10:54.818 --> 01:10:59.389
I WANTED TO ASK YOU
A FAVOR.

01:10:59.423 --> 01:11:02.592
YOU SEE, TODAY IS PRESTON'S
BIRTHDAY AND IF YOU SEE HIM,

01:11:02.626 --> 01:11:05.962
IF YOU COULD SEND HIM HOME
A LITTLE EARLY.

01:11:08.798 --> 01:11:11.801
LATELY HE'S BEEN
WORKING SO HARD.

01:11:11.835 --> 01:11:15.805
ALL OF A SUDDEN MONEY'S
BECOME SO IMPORTANT TO HIM.

01:11:15.839 --> 01:11:18.475
I GUESS THAT'S
MOSTLY MY FAULT.

01:11:18.508 --> 01:11:20.910
YOU DON'T HAVE KIDS,
DO YOU, MR. MACINTOSH ?

01:11:20.944 --> 01:11:25.915
I'LL TELL YOU,
IT'S VERY EASY TO MAKE
MISTAKES WITH THEM.

01:11:25.949 --> 01:11:30.520
I HAVEN'T ALWAYS PAID ENOUGH
ATTENTION TO MY KIDS.

01:11:30.554 --> 01:11:34.458
I PUSHED THEM
TOO HARD... MAYBE.

01:11:34.491 --> 01:11:36.860
ESPECIALLY PRESTON.

01:11:36.893 --> 01:11:39.496
I GUESS I EXPECT
MORE FROM HIM.

01:11:39.529 --> 01:11:44.601
HE REMINDS ME
OF MYSELF AT THAT AGE.
I COULDN'T WAIT TO GROW UP.

01:11:44.634 --> 01:11:48.738
I'M AFRAID HE'S MISSING OUT
ON HIS CHILDHOOD.

01:11:51.808 --> 01:11:53.843
SO AM I.

01:11:55.745 --> 01:11:59.683
WELL, THANKS.
I WON'T TAKE UP
ANY MORE OF YOUR TIME.

01:11:59.716 --> 01:12:04.621
AND WE APPRECIATE YOU
SENDING PRESTON HOME EARLY.

01:12:04.654 --> 01:12:08.458
IF-- IF HE WANTS TO COME,
THAT IS.

01:12:08.492 --> 01:12:11.995
[ Whispering ]
I WANT TO COME HOME.
THANKS.

01:12:12.028 --> 01:12:15.365
DAD. DAD ?

01:12:17.534 --> 01:12:19.836
DAD ?

01:12:19.869 --> 01:12:21.938
DAD ! DAD !

01:12:25.609 --> 01:12:27.577
DAD !

01:12:27.611 --> 01:12:29.846
DAD, WAIT !

01:12:29.879 --> 01:12:33.917
DADDY ! HENRY ?

01:12:33.950 --> 01:12:37.387
HENRY ! WAIT A MINUTE,
WHERE'S HENRY ?

01:12:37.421 --> 01:12:40.156
YOUR DRIVER ?
HE LEFT A LITTLE WHILE AGO.

01:12:40.189 --> 01:12:43.827
H-HE LEFT ?
YOU SURE IT WAS HENRY ?

01:12:43.860 --> 01:12:45.829
BIG GUY, WHITE LIMO.

01:12:45.862 --> 01:12:48.765
HE'S GONE.

01:12:50.467 --> 01:12:52.402
THANKS.

01:12:56.473 --> 01:12:59.776
NOW I KNOW
WHO MY FRIENDS ARE.

01:13:03.480 --> 01:13:06.883
EXCUSE ME. SORRY.

01:13:06.916 --> 01:13:09.586
[ Door Opening ]
[ Shay ]
PRESTON ?

01:13:09.619 --> 01:13:11.955
MR. MACINTOSH ?

01:13:13.723 --> 01:13:17.527
MR. MACINTOSH ?
IT'S JUST ME.

01:13:17.561 --> 01:13:20.797
WHICH ONE OF US
DID YOU WANT ?
I WAS LOOKING FOR YOU.

01:13:20.830 --> 01:13:24.768
OH, GOOD.
AND MR. MACINTOSH.

01:13:24.801 --> 01:13:28.705
LOOK, IT'S VERY, VERY
IMPORTANT THAT I FIND
MR. MACINTOSH RIGHT NOW.

01:13:28.738 --> 01:13:32.809
- DO YOU UNDERSTAND ?
- HE'S NOWHERE.

01:13:32.842 --> 01:13:36.580
HE'S GONE. I THINK
YOU'D BETTER LEAVE TOO.
PRESTON...

01:13:36.613 --> 01:13:40.484
YOU COULD BE IN DANGER.
JUST GO, OKAY ?

01:13:40.517 --> 01:13:44.353
YOU GOT YOUR NECKLACE.
JUST TAKE IT AND LEAVE.

01:13:46.756 --> 01:13:49.926
* GIVE IT BACK
THERE'S NO TIME TO LOSE *

01:13:49.959 --> 01:13:52.462
* SO GIVE IT BACK
GIVE IT BACK **

01:13:52.496 --> 01:13:55.765
RIGGS ? RIGGS ?
RIGGS ?

01:13:59.836 --> 01:14:01.805
LOOKS LIKE
NO ONE'S HOME.

01:14:01.838 --> 01:14:04.741
SHUT UP,
WIENERMAN.
BIDERMAN.

01:14:04.774 --> 01:14:06.476
WHERE IS HE ?
I DON'T KNOW, BUT HE MIGHT BE
DOWN THE STREET....

01:14:06.510 --> 01:14:08.945
AT MR. MACINTOSH'S,
THAT'S HIS BOSS.

01:14:08.978 --> 01:14:11.748
MACINTOSH.
COME ON !
[ Whimpering ]

01:14:11.781 --> 01:14:16.820
YOU KNOW, I DO LIKE
WHAT THEY HAVE DONE
WITH THIS COLOR.

01:14:18.387 --> 01:14:22.492
THERE YOU ARE, PUPPY-BUTT.
DID YOU GET ME MY MONEY ?

01:14:22.526 --> 01:14:25.161
UH, MACINTOSH
HAS DISAPPEARED.
WHAT ?

01:14:25.194 --> 01:14:27.964
NOW, I AM WARNING YOU,
TOM THUMB, DON'T YOU
TRIFLE WITH ME.

01:14:27.997 --> 01:14:30.867
IF I DON'T GET PAID,
I WILL SUE MR. MACINTOSH...

01:14:30.900 --> 01:14:33.803
FOR EVERY DIME
HE IS WORTH !

01:14:33.837 --> 01:14:36.806
WELL, BE SURE AND TELL ME
WHEN YOU FIND HIM.

01:14:36.840 --> 01:14:40.677
OKAY, LITTLE MR. MAN,
THIS PARTY IS OVER !

01:14:40.710 --> 01:14:44.814
QUIET ! STOP THAT PLAYING !
STOP THAT MUSIC ! QUIET !
ATTENTION ! ATTENTION !

01:14:44.848 --> 01:14:46.950
EVERYBODY,
THIS PARTY IS OVER !

01:14:46.983 --> 01:14:49.819
OUR HOST...
CAN'T PAY HIS BILLS !

01:14:49.853 --> 01:14:53.389
MR. MACINTOSH IS A FRAUD !
[ Woman ]
WHAT ?

01:14:53.422 --> 01:14:56.359
[ Crowd Murmuring ]
WHO'S THAT KID ?

01:14:56.392 --> 01:15:00.897
SHE'S RIGHT.
HATE TO TELL YOU THIS,

01:15:00.930 --> 01:15:04.634
BUT THERE'S BEEN
A TERRIBLE MISTAKE.

01:15:04.668 --> 01:15:06.536
NOBODY S-SHOULD
HAVE BEEN INVITED.

01:15:06.570 --> 01:15:09.539
MACINTOSH IS-- IS GONE.

01:15:09.573 --> 01:15:12.542
AND HE'S NOT COMING BACK.

01:15:12.576 --> 01:15:17.747
SO I THINK YOU SHOULD
ALL LEAVE TOO, SO GO. GO ON.

01:15:17.781 --> 01:15:22.351
CLOSE DOWN THE BAR !
COME ON, LET'S GET OUTTA HERE.

01:15:22.385 --> 01:15:24.353
COME ON, ANTOINE.
MOVE IT !

01:15:24.387 --> 01:15:26.756
COME ON, MOVE IT !

01:15:36.633 --> 01:15:39.569
COME BACK WITH THOSE GLASSES !
GIVE ME THAT !

01:15:39.603 --> 01:15:41.638
OH ! OH ! OH !

01:16:13.737 --> 01:16:15.805
[ Knocking ]

01:16:15.839 --> 01:16:19.475
HENRY ?

01:16:19.508 --> 01:16:22.746
HENRY !
I KNEW YOU'D COME BACK !

01:16:24.614 --> 01:16:26.549
HENRY--
[ Gasping ]

01:16:26.582 --> 01:16:29.719
HAPPY BIRTHDAY.
I'M HERE TO BLOW OUT
YOUR CANDLES.

01:16:29.753 --> 01:16:33.757
OH ! LET ME GO !
WHAT'S YOUR HURRY, KID ?
GOT A BIG CHECK TO CASH ?

01:16:37.961 --> 01:16:41.631
LET ME GO !
I LIKE THIS PAD.
WHAT DO YOU THINK, JUICE ?

01:16:41.665 --> 01:16:45.134
OH, YEAH, I LIKE THE PAD.
IT LOOKS REAL NICE.

01:16:45.168 --> 01:16:48.638
CAN YOU HANDLE IT ?
GOT THE TV, DRUMS.
OH, I LIKE THIS.

01:16:48.672 --> 01:16:50.640
TV, DRUMS.
ALL KINDS OF TOYS.

01:16:50.674 --> 01:16:54.143
HE'S GOT A LITTLE TASTE,
A LITTLE FLAVOR.
WHAT'S THIS THING HERE ?

01:16:54.177 --> 01:16:57.346
- I DON'T THINK
I'VE SEEN ONE OF THOSE BEFORE.
- HOW DO YOU WORK THIS ?

01:16:57.380 --> 01:17:00.784
WELL, YOU TURN THE KNOB--

01:17:00.817 --> 01:17:04.854
YOU REALLY SHOULDN'T LET HIM
IN SUCH A NICE HOUSE AS THIS.

01:17:04.888 --> 01:17:07.691
ALL YOUR STUFF
COULD GET BROKEN.

01:17:07.724 --> 01:17:09.859
KID, WHERE'S MACINTOSH ?

01:17:09.893 --> 01:17:12.829
N-NOWHERE.

01:17:12.862 --> 01:17:16.599
HE'S NOWHERE.
I'M GOING TO ASK YOU
ONE MORE TIME.

01:17:16.632 --> 01:17:19.368
WHERE IS HE ?
HUH !

01:17:19.402 --> 01:17:21.637
THERE IS NO MACINTOSH.

01:17:21.671 --> 01:17:24.874
I MADE HIM UP.
IT WAS ME THE WHOLE TIME.
DON'T GIVE ME THAT.

01:17:24.908 --> 01:17:27.543
WHO BOUGHT THIS HOUSE ?
I-I DID.

01:17:27.576 --> 01:17:30.146
YOU ? YOU OUTBID ME ?

01:17:30.179 --> 01:17:35.451
WAIT A MINUTE.
YOU TRYIN' TO TELL ME
THAT THIS LITTLE BOY HERE...

01:17:35.484 --> 01:17:37.954
OUTBID YOU
WITH YOUR OWN MONEY ?

01:17:37.987 --> 01:17:40.990
BE A FLY ON THE WALL,
OKAY, JUICE ?

01:17:41.024 --> 01:17:44.994
LISTEN, KID, YOU KNOW
IT'S ILLEGAL TO TAKE THINGS
THAT DON'T BELONG TO YOU.

01:17:45.028 --> 01:17:49.465
I KNOW. I FEEL AWFUL.
TAKE ME TO THE POLICE.

01:17:49.498 --> 01:17:54.003
CARL, DON'T DO IT.
IT'S A TRICK.
GET OUTTA HERE.

01:17:54.037 --> 01:17:57.841
SON, I DON'T WANT
TO TAKE YOU TO THE POLICE.
JUST TELL ME, OKAY ?

01:17:57.874 --> 01:18:00.844
WHERE'S MY MONEY ?

01:18:00.877 --> 01:18:03.847
I-I SPENT IT.

01:18:03.880 --> 01:18:09.485
- ALL OF IT ?
- ALL OF IT.

01:18:09.518 --> 01:18:11.888
HOW COULD YOU SPEND...

01:18:11.921 --> 01:18:15.825
A MILLION DOLLARS
IN SIX DAYS ?

01:18:15.859 --> 01:18:18.828
YOU MUST NOT HAVE BEEN
SHOPPING LATELY.

01:18:18.862 --> 01:18:22.165
CARL, CARL,
WAIT A MINUTE.

01:18:22.198 --> 01:18:25.668
MAYBE WE'RE THINKING ABOUT
THIS MACINTOSH THING
IN THE WRONG WAY.

01:18:25.701 --> 01:18:28.838
WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT ?
YOU NEEDED A NEW HOUSE,
A NEW IDENTITY.

01:18:28.872 --> 01:18:31.440
THIS KID,
HE'S DONE IT FOR YOU.

01:18:31.474 --> 01:18:34.510
I MEAN, MACINTOSH
COULD RUN FOR MAYOR HERE.

01:18:34.543 --> 01:18:37.713
YEAH, I KIND OF LIKE
THE IDEA OF THAT--
MAYOR QUIGLEY.

01:18:37.747 --> 01:18:42.685
NO, NO,
MAYOR MACINTOSH.
I LIKE IT.

01:18:42.718 --> 01:18:46.455
LOOK, THERE'S ONLY ONE PROBLEM
WITH THAT. THE-- AAAH !

01:18:46.489 --> 01:18:48.524
HEY !
COME BACK HERE !

01:18:48.557 --> 01:18:51.460
WAIT FOR ME !
I'M COMING !
HE'S UPSTAIRS, MAN !

01:18:53.930 --> 01:18:56.565
BREAK IT DOWN !
BREAK IT DOWN !

01:18:56.599 --> 01:18:58.835
THERE HE IS !

01:19:01.737 --> 01:19:03.873
WHERE IS HE ?
WHERE IS HE ?
HE WENT DOWN THERE !

01:19:03.907 --> 01:19:06.375
JUICE, GO AFTER HIM !
I AIN'T GOIN' DOWN THERE.

01:19:06.409 --> 01:19:08.444
GO ON ! NOW !
YOU'RE CRAZY.
I AIN'T GOIN' DOWN THERE.

01:19:08.477 --> 01:19:11.580
WATCH YOUR HEAD.
WHAT IS IT, ABOUT 230--
WHOA !

01:19:11.614 --> 01:19:14.517
AAAH !
I'M NOT GOIN' IN THERE.

01:19:18.487 --> 01:19:21.590
OH, NO, HE DIDN'T.
DID YOU SEE HIM ?

01:19:21.624 --> 01:19:25.761
OH, NO, YOU DID
JUST PUSH ME IN THE POOL !
GET OUT, WE GOTTA FIND HIM !

01:19:26.963 --> 01:19:29.799
WHAT ?

01:19:29.833 --> 01:19:32.601
WHAT HAPPENED ?

01:19:34.370 --> 01:19:36.840
ACT LIKE YOU GOT
A PURPOSE IN LIFE. GO.

01:19:36.873 --> 01:19:39.943
[ Biderman ]
I THINK I'M EXPERIENCING
CHEST PAINS.

01:19:49.853 --> 01:19:51.855
[ Indistinct Noise ]

01:19:55.524 --> 01:19:58.862
CARL ? JUICE ?

01:19:58.895 --> 01:20:01.697
HUH ? OH.

01:20:10.706 --> 01:20:13.877
LITTLE BOY ?
LITTLE BOY FROM THE BANK ?

01:20:25.855 --> 01:20:28.457
HA, HA.

01:20:28.491 --> 01:20:30.927
OH !
[ Groaning, Grunting ]

01:20:34.397 --> 01:20:36.399
WHERE AM I ?
OH-OH !

01:20:37.400 --> 01:20:39.969
OOH ! OOH !
OOH ! OOH !

01:20:40.003 --> 01:20:43.907
[ Sheep Bleating,
Cow Mooing ]

01:20:44.941 --> 01:20:48.912
[ Muttering ]

01:20:48.945 --> 01:20:51.881
[ Rooster Crowing ]

01:20:51.915 --> 01:20:54.383
HEY, HEY !
[ Cow Mooing ]

01:21:02.926 --> 01:21:05.361
GOT YA ! UH-HUH !

01:21:06.930 --> 01:21:09.598
- HEY !
- GOT HIM.

01:21:10.866 --> 01:21:12.835
IT'S TIME FOR
A LITTLE BATTING PRACTICE.

01:21:12.868 --> 01:21:15.738
HERE WE GO !

01:21:15.771 --> 01:21:18.674
HEY ! WHAT'S HAPPENING ?
WHOA ! HEY !

01:21:18.707 --> 01:21:21.844
JUST OUTSIDE.
LET'S TRY A SINKER.
A SINKER !

01:21:21.877 --> 01:21:24.713
